title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Form into a loaf and place in baking pan with lid.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
About 20 minutes before time is done, remove lid.
Let bake, uncovered, for remaining time.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in salt water.
Drain.
Mix cheese, butter and celery soup until melted together.
Place in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put bread crumbs with dots of butter on top before baking.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain. Preheat oven to 375°. In medium saucepan, melt margarine; stir in flour and salt. Gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir until mixture thickens slightly (mixture should coat spoon). Remove from heat. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese and stir until melted. Pour cooked macaroni into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Add cheese mixture and mix well. Top with remaining cheese. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Put all in a casserole.
Bake one hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Precook green pepper cups in boiling water (salted), about 5 minutes.
Sprinkle inside with salt. Brown meat and onion.
Add stewed tomatoes, rice, Worcestershire and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and simmer until rice is almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Stuff peppers and stand upright in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch cooking dish.
Bake uncovered and sprinkle with more cheese.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; set aside for 20 minutes.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir together the flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Stir into the creamed mixture, along with the vanilla and soaked oats.
Pour batter into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl with fork until crumbly. Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until set.

title: elegant sweet potatoes
directions: Cut the boiled sweet potatoes in half or into thick rounds. Place them in a baking pan.
Dot with butter or margarine and sprinkle with brown sugar to which the coconut flavoring has been well blended.
Stir it well so that the coconut flavoring is mixed evenly throughout the brown sugar.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together and serve as spread for party sandwiches or as a party spread with crackers.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread evenly over crust. Bake according to crust directions.

title: crab spread
directions: Warm soup in sauce pan. Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons cold water. Add to warm soup. Stir in cream cheese to melt; stir in mayonnaise. Add celery, onion and crab. Pour into mold and chill until set. Serve with crackers. Makes 1 quart.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Simmer just until tomatoes juice.
Add some V-8 and simmer until it thickens, which will just be a bit.
Add freshly ground pepper, salt and basil. Cook the mostaccioli until about tender. Serve with tossed salad and bread.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Follow cake mix directions to make a 3 layer cake.
Punch holes in cool cake.
Mix Pet milk, strawberries and Jell-O.
Set aside.
Place cake layer in punch bowl.
Top with Jell-O mixture (Pet milk, strawberries and Jell-O).
Put Cool Whip on top of Jell-O mixture.
Repeat until all three layers have been done. Refrigerate and chill until ready to serve.

title: quick lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and parsley.
Spray dish with Pam.

title: hattie's sauerkraut relish
directions: Chop up sauerkraut until very fine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack into jars with lid on.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add sugar and continue to beat until meringue stands in stiff peaks. Fold in vanilla. Drop by teaspoonful about 1-inch apart on well-greased cookie sheet. Bake in slow oven (250°) for 40 to 50 minutes until cookies are firm but not brown. Remove at once from cookie sheet to wire racks. When cookies have cooled completely, store in a tightly covered container. Makes 30 cookies.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Crush cornflakes and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Add more water if needed.
Cook until meat and vegetables are tender, about 2 hours.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Rinse in cold water. Place in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight. Yields
12 to 14 servings.

title: graham cracker yum!
directions: You will also need 1 large baking sheet (lined with aluminum foil) lined with graham crackers.

title: hot pineapple rum
directions: Warm pineapple juice with honey until honey is dissolved. Remove from heat; add rum and serve.
Serves 8.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions and butter until golden; do not brown.
Add 2 cans of beef broth and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Place soup into individual ovenproof bowls or crocks and top with croutons or slice of bread and a slice of Mozzarella cheese (may substitute Muenster).
Broil until cheese is melted and very lightly browned. Makes 4 servings.

title: mom's antipasta salad
directions: Put lettuce on plate and put other ingredients over top of lettuce, and then make up Good Seasons salad dressing on envelope, then pour over top of the salad, and let sit for 1 hour, then serve cold.

title: jean's pepper slaw
directions: Shred
cabbage,
peppers
and onions together.	Soak in ice water
with
cup
salt
(3 hours); drain.
Mix sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cover cabbage mixture with liquid mixture and heat to boil point; do not boil.
Pack in clean pint jars and seal.

title: low fat banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Then mix eagle brand milk and Cool Whip.
Cut banana into slices.
Layer beginning with wafers.
Easy and the best part is, you can't tell it's lowfat and neither can anyone else!!!

title: pink punch
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O.
When gelatin is dissolved, add cold water, fruit juices and sugar.
Chill. When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Frozen strawberries, cherries or banana slices may be added.

title: rice dressing
directions: Grind all of above together; cook over low heat in black pot for about 2 hours.
Season with salt, black and red pepper to taste.
Cook 6 pounds rice; add to dressing mix; stir well and serve.

title: cherry surprise cake
directions: Beat sugar and oil together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Combine flour with baking powder; add vanilla. Beat all together.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of batter in pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
Add rest of the batter. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon for topping.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet.
Add taco seasoning package and prepare according to directions.
When finished, pour into casserole serving dish.

title: carnation 5 minute fudge
directions: Combine milk, butter and sugar in pan; heat to boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate morsels and vanilla; stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 x 9-inch pan. Garnish with nuts.
Cool and cut.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook
onion and garlic in chicken broth until onion and garlic are tender.
Add soups and cheese.	Simmer until cheese is melted,
stirring frequently.
Grease casserole dish.
Add layer dry
noodles
and layer coarse, chopped chicken.
Cover with sauce.
Add layers until you fill casserole, ending with sauce. Cover
and	cook
at 275° for 1 hour until noodles are tender.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Put into 1-quart ungreased casserole.
Top with stuffing mix rolled in melted butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Put all in a bowl and mix it up.
Bake 1 hour.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Dice tomato and add onion.
Cut up avocados in small pieces. Add remaining ingredients.
Mash with potato masher until blended.

title: diane's marinara sauce
directions: Dice onion and press garlic in boiler.
Cover with 1/2 inch water.
Cook until onions are soft.
Add crushed tomatoes.
Do not add extra water.
Add all seasonings to taste.
Cover and simmer at least 3 hours.
Serve over large noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Stir in dry ingredients, except sesame seed.
Chill for 1 hour. Pinch off about the size of a walnut; shape into fingers.
Roll in milk, then sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes (ungreased cookie sheet).

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix all and sprinkle 1/2 cup sharp Cheddar cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour (until heated through).
Serves 8.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion about 5 minutes and drain.
Combine stuffing mix with melted butter.
Combine sour cream with cream of chicken soup and carrots.
Fold into squash.
Place 1/2 the stuffing mixture into casserole.
Spread squash mixture on top and cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done; drain.
Add the remainder of ingredients, except bacon bits.
Refrigerate for 6 hours.
When ready to serve, put bacon bits on top.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix the soup and sour cream.
In a baking dish, spread chicken pieces and top with soup mixture. Repeat. Mix the remaining ingredients together and spread over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Put zucchini and carrots in enough boiling water to cover. Cover pan and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender; drain.
In large saucepan, saute onion in 4 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing mix, soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.

title: grandma's oyster snack
directions: Mix oil and all the seasonings together and heat to boiling. Pour over crackers and toss well.
Store in a covered plastic container.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in pan; boil.
Remove from heat and stir in oats, vanilla, peanut butter and coconut. Place by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: best rolls
directions: Get milk medium warm.
Add Crisco and sugar.
Stir until Crisco melts.
Let milk mixture get really cool.
Add dissolved yeast and 1/2 of the flour.
Let rise until double.

title: cabbage ramen noodle salad
directions: Brown noodles, sesame seed and almonds in margarine.
Cool. Toss with cabbage and onions.
Heat oil, vinegar, sugar, seasoning, pepper and soy sauce, stirring, just until sugar dissolves.
Chill.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Cut each chicken breast in 4 or 5 pieces.
Saute in 2 T. vegetable oil.
Add soup, milk, lemon juice and lemon pepper. Serve over hot noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: brussels sprouts and pearl onions
directions: Saute sprouts in butter in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat until golden (about 5 minutes).
Add onions and cook two minutes; add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cook one minute, stirring in broth.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, covered, until sprouts are tender (5 to 7 minutes).

title: chili(for 25)
directions: Mince garlic.
Saute beef, onions and celery until beef is brown.
Pour off grease.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, sugar, salt, cumin and kidney beans.
Simmer 1 hour.
If desired, tomato paste can be added.

title: fresh strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Fold in Cool Whip and strawberries.
Chill.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes almost 2 cups dressing.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped pecans. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add sugar to ground cranberries.
Let set overnight.
Drain and add grapes and nuts.
Just before serving add whipped topping.

title: moist cornbread
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch metal pan with peanut oil.

Cream the butter, sugar and egg yolks. Beat the egg whites until stiff. Sift the flour, baking powder and salt. Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with the warm milk. Stir in the cornmeal.
Fold in the egg whites.
Put either into prepared metal pan or muffin cups lined with papers. Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter.
Press firmly into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine margarine, powdered sugar, eggs, vanilla and cream cheese; mix well.
Spread mixture over the crumbs.
Place, in layers, over cream cheese mixture, as follows: bananas, pineapple, Cool Whip and pecans.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and one egg in a bowl.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonful into powdered sugar. Roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Remove from sheet and cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: extra sweet pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Beat eggs in large bowl. Once eggs are beaten, add and mix sugar (or Splenda), salt, cinnamon, pumpkin pie spice and condensed milk. Stir

pumpkin into mixture. Gradually stir in evaporated milk. After mixing well, pour into pie shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350°. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Allow to cool. Great with a scoop or two of whipped cream!!!

title: golden pound cake
directions: Step 1:
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together. Set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks are formed.

title: freezer biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast to lukewarm milk.
Mix milk and yeast with flour mixture.
Knead. Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with small biscuit cutter (or cookie cutter; I use heart shaped).
Dip biscuit in melted butter.
Put two together.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or brown slightly then freeze.
Brown biscuits before serving.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix peanut butter and melted butter with spoon.
Add powdered sugar; knead until smooth.
Put a small amount of melted chocolate into mold.
Add peanut butter mixture and cover with more chocolate.
Put in freezer for 4 minutes, then turn mold over and tap finished candy onto table.

title: english muffin appetizers
directions: Toast English muffins.
Mix other ingredients in bowl.
Spread onto English muffins.
Place under broiler until cheese melts and is slightly browned.
Cut into quarters.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Pressure cook roast for 30 minutes or bake in the oven for 2 1/2 hours.
Cut roast in small pieces.
Drain meat.
Add veggies. Add juice and tomatoes.
Stir, then cover and simmer 40 minutes.

title: chocolate surprise cupcakes
directions: Mix together until fluffy the cream cheese, egg, white sugar and salt.
Add chocolate chips to mixture.
Drop one heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese-chocolate chip mixture into each cupcake.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost when cool, if desired.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Heat oleo and cheese over low heat until cheese melts.
Add crab.
Serve with Triscuits.

title: pear and grape salad
directions: Arrange spinach on platter.
Place pears pinwheel fashion on top.
Dot with grapes, celery and pecans.
Combine yogurt and preserves and serve with salad.
Serves 4 with 140 calories and 3 grams fat per serving.

title: sandra's chocolate gravy
directions: Melt butter or oleo in skillet.
Add flour; stir well.
Add remaining ingredients; cook and stir until thick.
Serve on hot biscuits.

title: cheese club sandwich
directions: Set oven control to broil at 550°.
For each sandwich, broil bread slices 5-inches from heat until golden brown on 1 side. Spread with margarine or butter.
Top with tomato slice.
Place bacon on tomato and top with cheese. Broil until cheese is melted. Makes 1 sandwich.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Pour over sugar, salt and shortening.
Beat one egg.
Add to milk mixture, then add yeast.
Add enough flour to make a thick batter.
Beat until smooth.
Add the rest of the flour.
Put in a greased bowl and let dough rise until double in bulk.
Remove from bowl and knead on floured surface.
Shape into rolls.
Place in a greased baking pan.
Let rise to double in bulk (for about 1 hour).
Bake until brown in 350° oven.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Grease dish and place apples in bottom.
Mix cheese, sugar, flour and milk.
Cover apples with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good as a side dish or with Cool Whip as a dessert.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into small balls.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter together. Add sugars; beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour and blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Press with fork for crisscross effect. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until done.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple with juice.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine and cook 5 to 6 minutes the first 4 ingredients; remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin and food coloring.
Place washed, stemmed and drained strawberries in baked pie crust.
Pour glaze over berries.
Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: seafood naples(serves 4 people)
directions: Lightly dust shrimp and scallops with flour.
In heavy saucepan, heat olive oil.
Add seafood and brown lightly on both sides.
Add garlic and white wine; reduce for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add tomato sauce; simmer for 2 to 3 minutes and serve over hot pasta. Garnish with fresh basil leaves.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut up chicken breasts into small squares.
Melt butter over the chicken and roll in mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 400° for 15 minutes.
(This can be frozen before cooked.)

title: oven-fried tennessee chicken
directions: Melt butter (or shortening) in a shallow baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2, in a 375° oven. Coat pieces of chicken with seasoned flour in a paper sack. Place chicken in dish, then turn over to coat both sides with butter and bake, skin side down, in a single layer for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake another 30 minutes, until tender.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in fruit cocktail.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In small bowl, mix brown sugar, walnuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Dot with margarine. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Bring to a boil while stirring. Cook until thick and clear.
Add jello and a little red food coloring.
Stir in.
Let cool.
Add strawberries to baked pie shell.
Pour the cooled glaze over the strawberries and chill in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: one pan tomato basil chicken
directions: In large skillet, saute Rice-A-Roni according to package. Stir in 2 cups water, chicken and contents of seasoning packet. Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce to low and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli, tomato and basil.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler. Add pimento, milk, vinegar, sugar and egg.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Let cool and add 1 cup mayonnaise.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute in oleo the onion and green pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and pour into a large buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles in center.

title: cheaters-chocolate-chip cookies
directions: Slice cookie dough 1/2-inch thick and then quarter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Serve warm with glass of milk.

title: chicken casserole delight
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery until tender.
Add dry ingredients and stir well.
Add milk, chicken broth and water; stir well.

title: sailor punch a la mode
directions: Combine chilled grape juice and carbonated water in punch bowl.
Float scoopfuls of vanilla ice cream on top.
Serves about 25.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream the margarine; add sugar and egg yolks.
Mix in the lemon juice, flour and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes one 9-inch pie. Double all ingredients except lemon juice for 2 pies.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and soda.
Cut in butter with a fork until mixture looks like fine crumbs.
(Add raisins here.) Add buttermilk and mix with fork until dry ingredients are moist. Turn out on lightly floured board and knead gently for one minute until smooth.
Shape into a ball and place on prepared cookie sheet.
Flatten into 7 inch circle, dough will be about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Press a large floured knife into center, almost through to bottom.
Repeat at right angles to divide dough into quarters.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until top is golden and loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Remove loaf to wire rack and brush top with melted butter.
Dust with flour if desired.

title: cinnamon pull-aparts
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Place nuts in the bottom.
Cut the biscuit into quarters.
Roll each quarter in cinnamon sugar mixture.
Arrange in the pan.
Melt the margarine.
Mix brown sugar.
Pour over the sugared biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: hamburger goop
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add soup, salt and pepper.
Mix well and cook until soup is mixed through hamburger.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in saucepan until blended about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Mix well. Spread in an 8 x 8 x 2 inch pan.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, oleo, and vanilla in blender on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into 9 1/2-inch or 10-inch pie pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes and then sprinkle with coconut.
Serve warm or cold.

title: beef soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and other vegetables.
Cook on medium for about 30 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Toss nappa cabbage and onions; set aside.
Saute Ramen noodles, almonds and sesame seed in one stick of butter until lightly browned.
Set aside to cool.

title: marinated vegetables no. 2
directions: Combine prepared vegetables in a 1-quart jar.

title: applesauce raisin cake(yields 9 x 13-inch cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg, then applesauce.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to applesauce mixture and blend.
Stir in water and raisins.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.
Needs no icing.

title: kidney bean salad and dressing
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; add vinegar, egg and butter. Cook over low flame, stirring until thick.
Add beans, onion, celery, salt and pepper to warm mixture.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook slowly for at least 30 minutes.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon on wax paper. Place in refrigerator until set.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Grease baking dish; cut up 1 large onion and put in bottom of dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup rice on top of onion.
Cut up 1 chicken into serving pieces and lay on top of rice.
Salt and pepper to taste. Mix 1 can of celery soup and 1 can of cream of chicken soup with two cans of water and pour over all.
Bake, covered, 1 hour at 325°, or until tender.
Last few minutes, bake uncovered to brown a little.

title: molasses baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Combine all ingredients except bacon in a mixing bowl; mix well and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: In large saucepan, cook zucchini, crushed pineapple and lemon juice for 12 minutes.
Stir sugar into zucchini mixture and cook for 10 minutes; stir constantly.
Add apricot jello powder to zucchini mixture; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Place in glass containers.
Refrigerate until use.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add onions and saute, covered, on low heat for approximately 15 minutes.
Add sugar, salt and pepper, raising heat to a moderate temperature, cooking approximately 20 minutes.
Stir frequently until onions are a deep golden brown, but not burned.
Sprinkle with flour and cook 2 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
In a saucepan, add beef broth, Worcestershire sauce, parsley flakes and water.
Stir well, then add onions.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Put cheese into bottom of soup bowls and pour onion soup mixture over cheese.
Garnish with croutons.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all throughly.
Shape into balls about the size of a quarter.
(I do mine smaller.)
Brown in a skillet on all sides. Drain on paper towel.
Pour off grease and add the sauce to skillet.

title: super quick sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in bottom of ungreased 8 x 9-inch round pan.
Remove dough from can.
Separate into 8 coils; do not unroll.
Place breadsticks in shallow dish. Combine sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Arrange coils sugared side down in pan.
Sprinkle with any remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 19 to 24 minutes or until deep, golden brown.
Cool 1 minute; invert onto serving plate.
Serve warm.
Yield:
8 rolls.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip well. Pour into pie crust. Top with cherry pie filling. Place in refrigerator.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and slowly stir in sugar.
Beat until smooth; add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, mixing well.
Cover dough and chill until firm enough to roll out.
Roll out on floured board, making dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutters and place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: ree's hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix the dressing, fruit spread and soup mix in a small bowl. Place chicken in a roaster and pour the mixture over the chicken. Cook for 3 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine
pumpkin,
sugar,
salt
and spices.
Mix well. Add milk,
beaten
eggs
and flavoring.
Pour into pie crust. Bake until
set in moderate oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Makes 1 pie.
This recipe can be used also for sweet potato or squash pies.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Sift flour once, measure and add baking powder and salt.
Sift this mixture again into a mixing bowl.
Cut in the shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk and stir until soft, wet dough is formed.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: In large saucepan, cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter and mix in cereal.
Press into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt semi-sweet and butterscotch morsels and spread over top of Rice Krispies mixture.
Chill until firm, cut into bars and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream shrimp and cream cheese together.
Add onion and mayonnaise.
Add milk slowly until right texture for dip.

title: cajun deep fried turkey
directions: Inject 1
ounce of marinade into each side of breast, 1 ounce into
each
thigh
and
ounce
into each drumstick. Sprinkle generously
with
black
pepper
and Tony's Chachere Creole seasoning.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight. Put enough peanut
oil
in large pot to cover turkey.
Heat to 350°.
Make sure
all
water
is
drained
from turkey cavity before frying. Fry
turkey
for
4 minutes per pound at 350°. This should be done outdoors with a fish cooker.
You'll never want to eat another baked turkey.
This is a Louisiana tradition!

title: nutritious chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and brown sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Combine 1 1/4 cups flour, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in remaining 1 cup flour, the oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Add one optional ingredient, if desired.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart, onto cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes (10 minutes makes a soft cookie, 15 minutes makes a crisp cookie); cool a minute on the cookie sheet.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on a rack.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large heavy pot or iron skillet, fry tomato paste in olive oil. Stir until sauce is purple in color and follows spoon when stirring. You may process all veggies, plus tomatoes and add to skillet. Bring to a boil and lower heat; simmer for 2 to 3 hours. Serve over spaghetti.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, bell pepper and salt and cover with water.
Put plate on top to hold the cucumbers down.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices in large preserving kettle.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables to liquid mixture.
Heat thoroughly, but do not bring to a boil. Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal.

title: rice
directions: Mix and pour into Pyrex.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°. Yields 6 servings.

title: banana cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add bananas.
Mix baking soda with sour milk and add.
Fold in flour.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes. Icing not necessary.

title: pumpkin bread(muffins)
directions: Beat nutmeg, cinnamon, sugar, oil, eggs and salt together. Add pumpkin, water, soda and flour.
One cup of nuts may be added. Grease and flour 3 coffee cake pans.
Divide batter.
Cook 1 to 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
It also makes 36 muffins in much less time. Can be frozen.

title: tangy green beans
directions: Combine mustard, sugar, margarine and salt.
Heat slowly, stirring constantly.
Stir in lemon juice and vinegar.
Pour over green beans (drained).
Heat thoroughly.

title: pizza pockets for snackmaster
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain before mixing.
Cut onion and bell pepper.
Put a little margarine on one side of all slices of bread.
Heat Snackmaster and lay bread with margarine side down.
Put ingredients on bread including the cheese and top with second slice of bread with margarine side up.
Close Snackmaster and cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 pizza pockets.

title: broccoli-peas casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Arrange broccoli in greased casserole dish.
Cover with layer of peas. Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, cheese, onion and eggs to make a sauce.
Pour half of sauce over broccoli and peas.
Add rest of broccoli and top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add melted margarine, sugar and syrup.
Mix well. Add pecans.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: deep dark chocolate cake(mixes in 5 minutes)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes. Stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Shape the ground beef mixture into a loaf or use a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole with spoon.
Cook at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: swiss potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and slice thinly or cut into bite size pieces. In a large bowl combine pinch of salt and pepper, vinegar, onions, oil, bacon and eggs.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach in microwave.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix all ingredients together.
Great on crackers.

title: one-bowl buttercream frosting
directions: *Hershey's cocoa:
1/3 cup for light flavor, 1/2 cup for medium flavor or 3/4 cup for dark flavor.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt the margarine and put in a large baking dish.
Then thoroughly mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour this on top of the butter.
Top with peaches and syrup.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: power cookies
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 minutes or until brown.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: wild tuna salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and cool.
Then, mix all ingredients together.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Put meat and onion in casserole dish on top of Tater Tots.
Mix soups.
Pour soups on top of meat. Cover with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: soft rolls
directions: Mix the yeast, water, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/3 cup flour in a medium bowl until the mixture forms a thick, gluey paste.
Cover the bowl tightly with plastic wrap; set it aside for 1 1/2 hours, or until the mixture is thick and frothy.

title: robert redford pie
directions: Make pudding and cool.
Blend peanut butter, sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Put 2/3 of mixture into pie shell.
Pour pudding over.
Cover with whipped topping.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture on top.
Chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli-cheese chicken
directions: In a skillet over medium heat in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes until brown on both sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Add broccoli.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes until chicken is fork-tender and broccoli flowerets are done, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.
Preparation time: 5 minutes. Cooking time:
25 minutes.
Serve with baked potato or wide noodles.

title: italian sausage and pasta bake
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Cut sausage into 1/2-inch pieces; discard casings. Cook sausage in skillet over medium heat until browned. Drain. Add onion, garlic and bell peppers; continue to cook until sausage is cooked through and vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally. Add tomatoes and tomato paste; mix well. Stir in pasta and basil. Transfer to 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Uncover; sprinkle cheese evenly over casserole. Continue to bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: caramel pies(makes 2)
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vanilla, butter and egg yolks.
Put 1 cup sugar in pan and brown; add milk and then add to the other mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake until done.
Top with meringue.

title: chicken with pasta and mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In saucepan, melt butter and dry dressing. Mix well. Add wine and mushroom soup. Mix well. Add cream cheese and mix until melted.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In medium saucepan, melt chips and margarine. Stir in crumbs and nuts. Press half the mixture
firmly into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Beat in Eagle Brand, vanilla and egg. Mix well.

Pour into prepared pan. Top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool to room temperature. Chill before cutting into bars. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cereal surprise cookies
directions: Heat chips and peanut butter in a heavy saucepan until the chips are melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal, marshmallows, and M&Ms.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.

title: easy cabbage casserole
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice like you would squash.
Roll in flour one piece at a time and fry until brown and done.
Real good.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring Karo, water and sugar to boil; add paraffin and peanuts and cook until peanuts turn amber in color (or until peanuts look parched).
Stir with wooden spoon often, while cooking in a black skillet.
Remove from stove and fold in soda and salt (which have been mixed together and lumps mashed).
Pour out on greased marble.
Before it gets too cool, mark with butcher knife into pieces.
Store in glass jars or containers.
Do not refrigerate. Makes at least two quarts of candy.

title: spoon bread
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, baking powder, salt, sugar and meal. Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Combine in bowl flour, sugar, eggs, salt, soda and sour cream.
Add boiled ingredients to flour ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet (large sheet with edge).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. While cake is baking, make frosting.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugars well.
Add eggs one at a time; then add other ingredients and bake in a greased tube cake pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: southern pork barbecue
directions: In large crock-pot, boil pork for 8 to 10 hours.
Use enough water to cover meat. Cool pork overnight. Reserve broth.

title: whole wheat snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter.
Add brown sugar and continue to beat for 1 minute.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients, then stir them into creamed mixture about one-third at a time.
With floured hands, roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll the balls in sugar and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, egg, shortening and water.
Blend well.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into pie pan.
Combine pie filling, lemon juice and spice.
Pour into center of batter; do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: crescent cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven
to
Separate
dough
into
long rectangles and place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan;
press over bottom and 1
inch up sides to form crust.
Press perforations to seal.
In
large
bowl
combine
remaining ingredients, mix well. Pour over dough.
Bake
at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until puffy and set.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar until well done.
Add jello and cook until dissolved.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: oven-fried drumsticks
directions: Melt shortening (part butter).
Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika in paper bag.
Heat oven to 425°.
Doing three or four at a time, shake in a bag to coat with flour, chicken legs.
Place chicken legs in a single layer in an oblong pan (12 x 9 1/2 x 2-inches).
Drizzle melted butter evenly over the chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Spoon into pie shell.
Spread mixture of cheese, egg, milk and Worcestershire sauce over top. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: fried turkey
directions: Heat all ingredients in microwave.
Inject all of the mixture in the turkey.
Rub stick of butter on outside of turkey. Sprinkle turkey with Tony's Creole seasoning and refrigerate turkey for 24 hours.
Cook at 350° for 3 1/2 minutes per pound.

title: master's marinade
directions: About 5 minutes before using, in medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Use to marinate any beef, shrimp or lamb before grilling.
Wonderful on Rib Eye steak.
You'll never use steak sauce again!

title: egg custard pie
directions: Grease and flour pie plate. Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie plate. Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: maple pecan pie
directions: Line a 10-inch pie plate with pecans.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Beat eggs and syrup in a separate bowl.
Add sour cream and whipping cream.
Beat until fluffy.
Add butter/sugar mixture; blend well.
Pour gently over pecans.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into ball and roll in 1 cup of the reserved walnuts.
Refrigerate for at least 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: lazy man's beef stew
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Put into it beef, carrots, tomato soup, bay leaf, 1/2 cup wine and onions.
Cover and bake in a 275° oven for 4 hours.
Remove from oven and stir (meat will be a little dry).
Add peas (still frozen), mushrooms (optional) and remaining 1/2 cup red wine and, if necessary, a little water.
Cook for 1 hour longer.
Serves 6.

title: swiss bliss
directions: Cut steak into 2 1/2-inch strips and brown.
Add other ingredients, except cornstarch and simmer 2 hours.
Use cornstarch to thicken gravy.
May be baked in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: italian venison kabobs
directions: Cut tenderloin into 1-inch cubes.
Marinate in Italian dressing for 8 hours or overnight.
Wrap each piece of tenderloin with 1/3 slice of bacon.
Place on a skewer and grill over hot coals.
Serve with potato and salad.

title: ham and asparagus pie
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in milk until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sauce comes to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into mayonnaise; then stir into hot mixture in saucepan. Add ham, asparagus and lemon juice.
Cook until heated.
Turn into a pastry shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil about 2 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: buckeyes
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients (everything but the semi-sweet chocolate) until well mixed.
Roll into 1 inch balls. Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Dip each ball in chocolate coating only half. Refrigerate.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.
105 calories per 4 dozen. 85 calories per each 5 dozen.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain corn.
Reserve liquid and add milk to make 1 cup. Combine all ingredients (can add any spices you like).
Stir and mix well.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Deep fry.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Makes approximately 12 to 15 corn fritters.

title: layered salad
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch Pyrex with chopped iceberg lettuce, then layer on top of lettuce as follows: green pepper, red pepper, celery, red onion, frozen peas, mayonnaise, cheese and bacon. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican dip appetizer
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco mix.
Spread onto cookie sheet.
Layer the toppings over cream cheese mixture. Use the nacho chips and veggies to dip.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Drain broccoli well.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 11 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.
This freezes well.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, molasses and oil.
Dissolve soda in water and add cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop from spoon and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: seasoned potatoes anna
directions: Cover sliced potatoes with water to prevent browning.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan and drizzle with 1 tablespoon oleo.
Pat potatoes dry and arrange 1/6 of them in overlapping layer in pan. Drizzle with 1 tablespoon oleo, then sprinkle with some cheese, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Press down to compress.
Cover with foil and bake on lowest rack 30 minutes in 425° oven. Uncover and continue baking 35 to 45 minutes until brown and crisp on edges.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Loosen edges and invert on platter.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in frying pan.
Drain.
In a large casserole dish, put hamburger in bottom, then layer potatoes and carrots, and top with Cheddar cheese.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken until tender.
Cook broccoli.
Remove chicken from bone, then layer chicken and broccoli alternately in a large casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Top with grated cheese and crushed potato chips.
Casserole can be made the night before but leave potato chips and cheese off until you are ready to put casserole in the oven.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 3-quart casserole, except margarine, cornflakes and almonds. Put margarine, cornflakes and almonds on top and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice meatball
directions: Mix hamburger meat and 1/2 cup of tomato sauce together. Make meatballs.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over meatballs; simmer on stove for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: fudge cake
directions: Heat the oleo, cocoa and milk in pan until oleo melts.
Add the powdered sugar, vanilla and chopped nuts.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Place crumbs in bottom of 2-quart casserole.
Mix pudding according to box directions.
Stir in the can of pumpkin; beat at low speed until just mixed.
Pour over crumbs; top with Cool Whip.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl using hands to stir.
Place in a loaf pan and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: leaf lettuce salad
directions: Bake sesame seed at 350° for 10 minutes, then add almonds for 10 minutes longer.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in boiler and boil until butter is melted and the taste is to your liking.
You may add some chopped onion to this if you like. Use small bottles of ketchup and Worcestershire sauce unless you want to make a lot of sauce.

title: sambo soup
directions: Brown hamburger until done.
Cook macaroni; drain.
Drain tomatoes.
Mix all together and serve with French bread.

title: heart smart sugar cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, egg, milk, and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Chill dough to make handling easier.
Make small rounded spoon size balls and flatten slightly on baking sheet.
Can sprinkle with additional sugar if desired.
(Dough can also be rolled out and cut out into shapes.) Bake at 375° for 8 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheets.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Spread on plate. Then pour one jar of chili sauce on top of cheese mixture. Sprinkle chopped crab meat over the top. Serve with 2 boxes of Triscuits.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix wet ingredients with dry ingredients and chill the dough.
After it is chilled, make balls the size of walnuts and roll them in the sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: slurch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
It will be slippery.
It's loads of fun for children to sit and play with.
Best if played with outside in the yard.

title: garden bean salad
directions: Drain all beans.
Place in a large bowl.
Add green pepper, celery, pimientos and green onions; set aside.
Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil in a saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Immediately pour over vegetables. Refrigerate several hours.

title: baked stuffed macaroni shells
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion, garlic and meat.
Pour off any fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper and oregano.
Bring to a boil and turn to low and cook 15 minutes. Meanwhile in medium bowl, mix cottage cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, parsley and nutmeg.
Heat oven to 350°.
Spread 2 1/2 cups tomato sauce mixture in baking dish.
Fill each shell with cheese mixture and arrange stuffed shells in dish.
Top with remaining sauce. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pizza bread
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add cheese and melt at low temperature. Add pizza sauce and remaining ingredients.
Spread on little party rye bread.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Cut the chicken into bite size pieces.
Slice celery into 1/2-inch pieces.
Skin carrots and slice into 1/2-inch pieces. Remove the core of the pepper and slice into pieces.
Mix sugar with the cornstarch and water.
Heat chicken in skillet.
Add pineapple and ginger; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple juice and 1/2 cup water; boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add celery and carrots; cook for 5 minutes.
Add pepper and sherry; mix well for 1 minute.
Thicken by adding cornstarch, sugar and water.
Serve over rice.

title: cinnamon bran muffins
directions: Combine cereal and milk, stir well and let stand 15 minutes. Combine flour, sugar, cereal and raisins, stirring just to moisten dry ingredients.
Fold in walnuts or berries.
Spray muffin tins with non-stick.
Fill 12 medium muffin cups 3/4 full with batter. Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.
Allow to sit 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip banana cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Set aside. Mix together banana, milk and vanilla. Set aside.

title: christmas strawberries
directions: Chop dates into small pieces.
Combine dates, coconut, sugar, butter, egg and salt in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and begins to boil (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in cereal, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Shape mixture to look like strawberries, using 2 teaspoons mixture for each.
Roll in red sugar crystals, coating heavily.
Pipe stems onto strawberries with green frosting.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: eileen's meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, egg and enough crumbs to hold together and form into bite-size balls.
Brown on all sides.
Combine chili sauce, jelly, lemon juice and brown sugar thoroughly; heat.
Add browned meat balls and serve in chafing dish.

title: alice swaim's broccoli salad
directions: Mix
broccoli,	cheese, onion and bacon.
Make sauce of vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli just before serving.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Line baking dish with 1/2 of vanilla wafers.
Spread cheese mixture over wafers. Top with cherry pie filling.
Spread Cool Whip over cherries.
Top with rest of wafers.
Let set 6 to 8 hours in refrigerator.
May use strawberry or blueberry.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil 1st four ingredients until thick. Then add jello, stir until dissolved. Set aside to cool. Cut strawberries in half and layer in the prepared pie shell. Pour cooled jello mixture over berries and chill in refrigerator at least 3 hours or until set.

title: cinnamon-raisin biscuits
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; cut in butter with pastry blender until it resembles coarse corn meal.
Add raisins and milk.
Stir in dry ingredients until moist.
Knead dough on floured surface 10 times.
Roll to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Combine yeast with lukewarm water.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients a little at a time until well mixed.
Refrigerate overnight before baking.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Can keep dough up to 2 weeks tightly covered in refrigerator.

title: bierocks
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and seasoning.
Cook cabbage until tender.
In the meantime, mix hot roll mix according to directions on box.
Roll out thin and cut into 6 inch circles.
Put in filling and cheese and close circle.
Seal edges together.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until rolls are brown.
Brush with melted butter.

title: peanut butter bears
directions: Mix with mixer, on medium speed, peanut butter, margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and eggs until smooth.
Reduce speed and beat 2 cups of the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
With a spoon, stir in remaining 2 cups of flour.
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Divide dough in half and set 1/2 aside.
On floured surface, roll out dough to 1/8 inch thick.
Cut with floured bear cookie cutter. Repeat until dough is used up.
Bake for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Decorate as desired.

title: hot dogs and dip
directions: Mix dip ingredients.
Cook hot dogs.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Put toothpicks in them.
Serve with dip.

title: cole slaw
directions: In a food processor or by hand, coarsely chop the cabbage and carrot.
In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, sugar, salt, and pepper.
Stir into cabbage mixture.
Chill until serving.

title: cottage cheese molded salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add salt and stir.
Add mayonnaise and stir.
Add milk and vinegar and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter chicken
directions: Mix the ingredients, except chicken, in a bowl.
Add the chicken to the mixture and chill for 3 hours.
Put 4 to 5 chicken pieces onto skewer.
Barbecue over open flame until thoroughly cooked.

title: sue's hot sauce
directions: Put in blender or food processor to blend and chop to combine. Turn switch on and off a couple times until desired size in pieces.
Do not overblend.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat cooker; add oil and brown meat.
Add onion, salt, pepper and water.
Place small potatoes, green beans, carrots and tomatoes over meat.
Close cover tightly.
Place pressure regulator on vent pipe and cook 10 minutes, with pressure regulator rocking slowly.
Cool cooker at once.
Make a paste of the flour and 1/4 cup water; stir into the stew to thicken.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter, egg yolks and bananas. Add flour which soda and baking powder have been sifted together, gradually. Add with milk. Fold in beaten egg whites last. Bake in a 350° oven about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bavarian mint coffee creamer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a container with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well to blend.
Store in an airtight container.
To serve, stir 2 tablespoons of creamer into 6 ounces of hot coffee. Yield: about 15 servings.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Boil raisins with water for 5 minutes.
Add sugar mixed with cornstarch, spices and salt.
Cook until thickens and then add vinegar.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Scramble eggs and add sausage. If using links, slice into buttons. Add onions, peppers and shredded cheese. Put all ingredients into soft shells and roll them up into burrito. Top with sour cream and picante sauce, of desired.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cook; run through tomato juicer.
Put on stove and cook until hot.
Seal in pint jars.
Pressure cook 10 minutes at 10 pound pressure.

title: polynesian grilled chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour over chicken breasts and marinate for at least 1 hour or overnight in the refrigerator.
Grill chicken on barbecue over medium-high heat approximately 20 minutes. Five minutes before removing from grill, place a slice of ham and cheese on top of each chicken breast.

title: joseph's coat salad
directions: Drain vegetables; set aside.
Mix vinegar and water together. Mix well the sugar, flour and mustard; add to vinegar and water. Cook until thick, then beat.
Pour hot sauce over vegetables and combine.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Let stand 24 hours in the refrigerator before serving.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix well with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cook pineapple, cornstarch and vinegar until thick.
When cool, add Equal.
Bake crust as on package.
Spread cheese; then add pineapple that's been thickened.
When cool, add the kiwi, banana and red grapes.
Better when refrigerated overnight.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream white sugar, brown sugar and shortening together.
Sift together baking powder, salt, soda and flour.
Add eggs alternately with flour to the creamed mixture.
Add coconut, gumdrops, quick oats and vanilla last to the dough.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix the soup with the chicken broth; bring to a boil.
Spray bottom of dish with Pam, then mix the Veg-All with chicken and place in bottom of dish.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Melt the margarine.
Add the salt, pepper, flour and buttermilk; mix well and spoon evenly over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until crust is done.

title: hobby house old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with a wire beater.
Pour into favorite pie crust recipe, using 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 375° until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients and bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix crisco, butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly with hands. Press and mold into a long smooth roll.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until stiff (several hours).
Cut into thin slices (1/8 to 1/16 inch) thick.
Place slices on ungreased baking sheet.

title: andagi(okinawan doughnuts)
directions: Mix flour, Bisquick and sugar together, then fold in the rest of the ingredients.
Do not mix as you would a cake mix.
Drop 1/2 tablespoonfuls (or smaller if desired) of dough into deep fat, cooking at medium heat.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot.

title: pecan kisses (candy)
directions: Mix beaten egg whites, brown sugar and vanilla flavoring well.
Coat each pecan half well with this mixture. Place on buttered cookie sheet, careful not to touch each other.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: camp cake
directions: Grease cake pan or large skillet.
Put marshmallows on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over marshmallows.
Spoon pie filling over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until marshmallows come to top and toast to light brown.
Or cover and cook over campfire until marshmallows come to top about 30 to 35 minutes.
Put Cool Whip on top of each hot serving.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: In a double boiler, melt chips and peanut butter.
Stir in milk and stir until thick.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let sit until set.

title: beef-broccoli pie
directions: In medium skillet, brown the beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in flour, salt and garlic salt.
Add 1 1/4 cups of milk and cream cheese.
Cook and stir until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Add a moderate amount of the hot cream mixture to the beaten egg. Return to mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture is thickened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in cooked broccoli.
Set aside.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound sirloin or tenderloin very thin and cut into near finger-shaped pieces.
Melt 1/2 the butter in a large heavy pan. Add onion , cook and stir until onion is tender.
Add beef, cook quickly, about 5 minutes, browning on all sides.
Set aside. Saute mushrooms in remaining butter.
Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg and add to beef.
Add cream, heat and season delicately to taste.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: bakers corn bread
directions: Pour boiling water over cornmeal and stir well, then add butter, sugar, salt, milk and eggs.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown on top.
Cool and cut.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Spread rice evenly in bottom of well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with one-fourth of onion soup mix.
Place chicken on rice; sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix and pepper.
Combine mushroom soup and chicken gumbo with water. Blend well and pour over chicken.
Dot with butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: butterfinger delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together.
Set aside.
Crush frozen Butterfingers in their wrappers with heavy object.
Put in bowl and set aside.

title: turkey rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; cut in the fat, then add the chopped parsley. Add milk to make a soft dough; knead lightly. Roll 1/2 inch thickness. Spread with cooked ground turkey which has been moistened with the stock in which the turkey was cooked. Roll up like a jelly roll and cut crosswise in 1 inch pieces. Bake in a hot oven at 400°. Serve with gravy over the tops of rolls. Makes 14 to 16 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift together and add to mixture the salt, baking powder and flour. Add vanilla.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 400° in preheated oven.

title: savannah crab stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper. Add mixture to milk. Add butter and stir until smooth and slightly thickened. Add Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice. Just before serving, add crabmeat and sherry. Serve in 2 large bowls or 4 small bowls.

title: crispy garden salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small bite size pieces.
Place in a bowl. Fill about 3/4 of the bowl with lettuce.
Peel the carrot and cucumber and cut into bite size pieces.
Cut the green pepper in half and take out the seeds.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Cut the tomato and celery into bite size pieces.
Put all vegetables in with the lettuce.
Toss until well mixed.
Enjoy!

title: italian steak
directions: Cook mushrooms, onion and green pepper.
Blend in chili sauce, water, salt, pepper and rest of ingredients.
Place steak in baking dish and cover with ingredients.
Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 300°, covering dish tightly.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough, otherwise just scrub good and rinse.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt, drizzle with butter and sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake another 10 to 15 minutes.
Check with fork.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cool; remove bones.
Boil celery, onion and green pepper in broth.
Add noodles and cook.
Mix remainder of ingredients.
Use bread crumbs for topping, then bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn chip tacos
directions: Cook beef and 1 large onion in a Dutch oven until meat is browned.
Drain.
Add next 9 ingredients; simmer 1 hour over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Arrange corn chips on serving plate. Spoon meat mixture over chips.
Layer with onion, green pepper, avocado, lettuce, tomato and olives.
Top with cheese.
Serve with taco or picante sauce.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Frozen broccoli, thaw and drain.
Put in large casserole dish. Layer Swiss cheese on top.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Spread over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until broccoli is tender.
Remove foil; sprinkle onions on top and bake additional 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and dice pickles bite-size.
Add onions, peppers and garlic.
Add salt and cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly. Let stand 3 hours; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over pickle mixture.
Heat just to a boil.
Put in jars and seal. You can use zucchini instead of pickles.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick margarine and graham cracker crumbs well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat 2 soft sticks margarine, 2 eggs and 2 cups powdered sugar with mixer at least 15 minutes.
The more you beat the creamier the filling.
Spread on crust.
Top with sliced bananas and pineapple.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Cover with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan; add brown sugar.
Cool.
Stir in eggs; blend well.
Add vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder. Stir in chocolate bits and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool. Cut into squares.

title: no peek popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously grease popover pans; do not use oil.
In small bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat until just blended; careful not to overbeat. Fill prepared cups half full of batter, about 1/3 cup.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Serve immediately.
If desired, serve from baking cups.
Yields 6 or 7 large popovers.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix shortening mixture with flour mixture and 4 tablespoons of milk.

title: zesty dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar and shake.
Chill.
Shake again just before serving.
Pour over lettuce wedges and sprinkle with chopped hard-cooked egg. Yield:
1 1/4 cups.

title: pizza fondue
directions: In a 2 qt. saucepan over medium heat, heat pizza sauce until hot.
Add cheese, a few cubes at a time, stirring after each addition until cheese is melted.
Do NOT boil.
Serve with cubed Italian bread or tortilla chips.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar and eggs; then add vanilla. Add 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt, being sure to break up lumps with fingers, then add 2nd cup flour.
Mix well with hands and roll out dough.
Bake 10 minutes at 350° on center and top racks on greased cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: small oatmeal cake(use 9-inch square pan)
directions: Pour over cake and spread evenly.
Put cake back in oven for about 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: grape juice punch
directions: Boil Imperial sugar and water until clear; cool.
Add fruit juices and chill.
Add ginger ale at serving time.
Pour over ice cubes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pinwheel sandwiches
directions: *Or can use 1 1/2 pounds of any one meat.

title: tuna noodle supreme
directions: Cook noodles per package directions and drain.
In a large bowl, stir together sour cream, mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, milk, mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended. Place mixture in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until they spread and turn brown.

title: good idea mandarin puffs
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a heavy-bottomed saucepan.
Add orange juice gradually, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the mixture comes together in one mass (very stiff).
Separately, whip egg yolks and to them by spoonfuls add the hot mixture.
Pour back into saucepan and cook over medium heat and boil several minutes.
Add yogurt and butter. Place a paper towel over the saucepan and then put the pan top on over it.
(This collects vapors that condense; good idea, eh?) Chill thoroughly.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries.
Add water and lemon juice to cherry juice to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Heat and pour over Jell-O.
Chill until partially gelled.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into mold. Chill until firmly set.

title: chocolate chip squares
directions: Freeze cookie dough.
Slice one roll into 40 (1/8-inch) slices. Arrange slices in a well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Press together to form bottom crust.
Set aside.
Beat cream cheese at high speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour mixture onto cookie layer.
Slice remaining dough into 40 slices; arrange over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cook; cut into squares.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: nut horns
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
In small saucepan heat milk to lukewarm (105° to 115°).
Stir in sugar and yeast. Let stand 10 minutes until bubbly.
Measure flour into large bowl. Add butter; cut in with pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor/fashion until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in yeast mixture and egg yolks; knead until dough is smooth.
Shape into a ball.
Set aside.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix sour cream, oil and eggs together.
Add corn.
Mix everything together.
Bake in a nine-inch glass baking dish for 25 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks, add milk and melted shortening.
Add flour mixture and stir.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Cook in pre-heated waffle iron.
Makes 4 waffles.

title: strawberry spread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve on Ritz crackers.
Great snack and very easy to make.
Really good.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop the peppers, onions and green tomatoes.
Combine with the vinegar; cook for 15 minutes, then set aside.
Mix together the sugar, water, salt, flour and celery seed; cook for 10 minutes. Add all this together, then add the mayonnaise and mustard.
Seal in jars.
Great for sandwiches or on crackers for snacks.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening and add buttermilk.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Pat to about 1/2-inch; cut and place on well-greased pan.
Bake in a 450° oven until brown.

title: orange jello
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Heat and dissolve jello.
Add cream cheese and beat.
Put in freezer until it begins to set, then beat with electric beater.
Add rest of ingredients and beat.
Makes big bowl.

title: gooey caramel cinnamon rolls
directions: Measure warm water into large mixer bowl.
Sprinkle yeast over water and add instant nonfat dry milk, sugar, oil, egg, salt and 1 1/2 cups of flour.
Turn on electric mixer and blend well, beating 3 minutes at medium speed on mixer.
Remove bowl from mixer stand and, by hand, gradually add 2 to 2 1/2 cups more flour to form a soft dough that you can handle, not stiff, but not sticky.
Beat dough well after each addition of flour to mix it in.
Knead one minute.
Roll dough into a 15 x 9-inch rectangle.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook until thick on medium-low heat.
Place in jars and seal.

title: chocolate-cherry crumb cake
directions: Make cake according to box directions, baking in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Make pudding.
Refrigerate.
After cake is done baking, let cool, then crumble the cake into fine crumbs; set aside.

title: pork chop scalloped potato casserole
directions: Brown chops in oil about 3 minutes on each side.
Remove, add onion rings to fat remaining in skillet.
Saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and reserve.
Melt butter in a medium pan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, add milk and broth slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Arrange sliced potatoes and chops in buttered (or sprayed with Pam) dish about 11 x 7 x 2-inch.
Top with onion rings.
Pour sauce evenly over potatoes, chops and onions.
Cover baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer or until chops and potatoes are tender.

title: white pizza
directions: Spread pizza dough in a pan.
Place slices of Provolone cheese on pizza to cover entire pizza, then add grated Mozzarella cheese to cover pizza.
Sprinkle on black olives and garlic powder to taste.

title: peach delight
directions: Pour peaches into bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, juice and all.
Sprinkle dry cake mix on top.
Add nuts and slice butter over nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring to boil, cover and let stand to cool.
Prepare pudding with cinnamon.
Fold in rice; let cool.

title: spinach pie
directions: Saute mushrooms, shallots and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg until juices evaporate, 10 to 12 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup wine.
Stir often about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rest of wine.
Set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon slices.
Place in a casserole dish or an oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, checking to make sure beans are not drying out.
When they are done, crumble bacon across the top.

title: quick pasta sauce
directions: Place all ingredients into pot.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not add bouillon, if you will be adding your own cooked meatballs or sausage.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in oleo in a skillet.
Add this to the eggplant.
Blend in salt, pepper and cheese.
Add the olives.
Pour into a 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Put in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs on high speed until light (about 4 minutes).
Add powdered sugar, softened butter and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes.
Spread over crumbs. Chill 30 minutes.
Spread pineapple over creamed mixture.
Arrange bananas over pineapple. Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Garnish with cherries.

title: scalloped cheese
directions: Butter the bread and cut into small pieces.
Arrange it in a small baking dish alternating with the cheese, using bread for the bottom and top layers.
Beat the eggs slightly and add the milk and salt.
Cover the bread with the mixture adding more milk, if necessary.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange nut balls
directions: Mix everything together and form into balls.
Roll in coconut or powdered sugar.

title: lazy day overnight lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add sauce and water. Blend and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix the first four ingredients together.
Top with margarine and enough crumbled Ritz crackers to absorb all margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Put dates, sugar and water in a saucepan and cook until thick. Add nuts and cool.
Cream the brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Beat in flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Chill dough.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Line a square pan with plastic wrap.
Pull up with plastic wrap to take out finished fudge.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix everything together and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Roll into balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake 9 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: *chocolate cream frosting
directions: Mix chocolate over warm water.
Mix cream cheese and milk together until well blended.
Add vanilla, salt and sugar; mix well.
Add chocolate.
Beat until creamy.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Prepare the night before and chill.

title: grilled ranch bread
directions: Combine the butter or margarine with the Ranch dressing mix. Slice the loaves of French bread lengthwise; spread tops with butter mixture.
Place bread until broiler (or cut surface down on grill) until crispy and golden brown.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine chili sauce and jelly.
Heat on low while stirring to melt jelly and blend well with chili sauce.
After well blended, add frozen meatballs and heat until thawed.
This usually takes about 30 minutes.
You also want the meatballs to absorb the flavor, so the longer they heat, the better they taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into ball.
Roll in chopped parsley, pecans or dried beef.

title: seafood cheese round
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayo, lemon juice, garlic and Worcestershire sauce together.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add celery and mix with spoon.
Form mixture into a flat circle about an inch high and the size of a plate.
Mix chili sauce and pickle relish.
Put on top of cheese mixture.
Place crab meat in middle and place shrimp around the crab meat on top of the chili sauce mixture.
Serve with crackers.

title: honey-mustard dip
directions: In a small bowl, with fork or wire whisk, mix the Dijon mustard, honey, soy sauce, minced green onion and minced peeled ginger root.

title: healthy three grain muffins
directions: Mix whole wheat flour with baking powder, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Soak All-Bran and oatmeal with milk.
A small amount more of milk may be needed to improve consistency.
Mix egg whites, oil and vanilla.
Combine all ingredients; stir just enough to moisten.
Fold in raisins.
Pour batter evenly into muffin pans.
Coat muffin pans lightly with vegetable oil spray such as Pam.

title: texas red chili
directions: Here's a version a cook from a ranch down by the Rio Grande gave the cowboys for something hot when traveling north of the Red River.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese in 2 1/2-quart bowl until smooth.
Beat in sour cream, sugar and salt on low speed.
Cut apricot halves in half.
Reserve a few cherries for garnish.
Stir apricots, remaining cherries, the pineapple and marshmallows into cheese mixture.
Pour into 4 1/2-cup mold or 6 individual molds.
Cover and freeze at least 8 hours.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Rinse, shell and devein shrimp.
Heat oil over high heat in a 4-quart saucepan.
Add onions, celery and bell pepper.
Cook until tender.
