Add garlic, bay leaf and Creole seasoning; stir well.
Add Tabasco sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes; reduce heat to low and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining water. Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and cook until pink and plump, 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In wok or skillet, heat oil, then cook chicken until done. Add onion and pepper; stir and cook 2 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons water to stir-fry mix to dissolve.
Put in skillet and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Prepare tortillas according to package directions.
Put small amount of chicken mixture down center of tortilla and fold up envelope style.
Serves 4.
Prep time:
30 minutes.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread into a 9x13 inch baking dish which has been lightly sprayed with cooking spray.

title: baked crab
directions: Saute onions, celery and pepper in butter.
Mix crab meat and dressing mix to cooked seasoning.
Add mustard, mayonnaise, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Pack into well-greased shell; top lightly with bread crumbs and a little butter.
Bake in oven at 400° until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.

title: sauce picante
directions: Into medium size saucepan place ground meat, onion and tomato sauce.
Heat on high about 10 minutes, then simmer for about 20 minutes until onion is fully cooked.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Cool slightly.
Add the rest of the ingredients and pour into a mold.
Refrigerate.
(Goes well with ham.)

title: turkey chow mein casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Gradually stir broth into baking mix in ungreased 1/2-quart casserole.
(Mixture will be slightly lumpy.) Stir in remaining ingredients except chow mein noodles.
Bake uncovered until thick and bubbly, about 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with the noodles.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with soy sauce, if desired.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: chicken-almond puffs
directions: Makes 4 to 5 dozen puffs.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet and set aside.
In saucepan over low heat, heat butter and broth until butter is melted.
In small bowl, stir together flour, salt and mixture all at once to saucepan.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball and pulls away from sides of saucepan.
Remove pan from heat; cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Continue beating until thick and glossy dough is formed.
Stir in chicken, almonds and paprika.
Drop by small teaspoon onto prepared baking sheet; bake for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 10 minutes, or until puffs are golden brown.

title: aloha quick bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each is added. Beat in banana, milk and extracts.

title: crab and rice primavera
directions: Bring vegetables and water to a boil in a medium saucepan, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Add milk, crabmeat, butter, garlic salt and basil.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and cheese.
Cover, remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork before serving.
May substitute imitation crabmeat.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend in blender. Add 1 can salad shrimp-spooning them into above mixture.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Layer bottom with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with milk; blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over graham crackers.
Layer with whole graham crackers again.
Pour rest of mixture over graham crackers.
Layer once more with graham crackers.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes and stir in all ingredients except cereal. Dip out by spoonfuls and roll in crushed sugar Frosted Flakes. Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375° or until heated through.
Serves 4.

title: herbed oven potatoes
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Add potatoes, a few at a time; toss to coat. Place in a single layer in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Drizzle with remaining oil mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 50 to 55 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Sprinkle with parsley. Yield: 6 servings.

title: florida pudding dessert
directions: Blend together and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: bagels
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt and 1/4 cup sugar, stirring to dissolve.
Gradually add flour, enough to make a soft dough, mixing well after each addition so that dough is well blended.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wiener casserole
directions: Cut up half of franks and mix in with other ingredients. Put in dish and bake, topped with whole wieners, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated veggies
directions: Blend vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper and pour over vegetables.
Let sit overnight.
Do not drain vegetables before serving.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Beat cream cheese with sugar until well blended.
Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful cheese mixture into each cupcake.
Bake 20 or 25 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned noodles
directions: Add salt and milk to beaten egg; add flour until dough can be handled; knead for 1 minute.
Roll out dough on a floured board as thin as possible.
Cut in strips and place in soup or boiling broth.
Cook until tender.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and allow to cool and partially congeal.
Combine cheese, cut cherries and pineapple and add to Jell-O.
Fold in Cool Whip.
(I use less than 8 ounces of Cool Whip.)

title: ham and cheese pie
directions: Place in pastry shell the ham and cheese cubes.
Mix together the remaining ingredients and pour mixture over ham and cheese in pastry.
Bake at 325° for 50-60 minutes.
Can also substitute chopped green pepper or chives for parsley if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge ice cream pie
directions: Spread 1/3 cup of hot fudge topping (at room temperature) over bottom of pie crust.
Place in freezer to chill.
Meanwhile, soften ice cream and mix with peanut butter.
Spoon into pie crust and freeze several hours or overnight.
Cover with plastic wrap when firm.
To serve, remove pie from freezer 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Heat remaining fudge sauce according to manufacturer's directions.
Serve each pie wedge with warm fudge sauce.

title: potato volcano
directions: Make a mountain of potatoes with a crater on top.
Put cheese in crater and drizzle on sides.
Drop bacon pieces all over.

title: mock rumaki
directions: You will need wooden toothpicks.

title: zucchini squash casserole(vegetable)
directions: Dice squash; cook in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Dice onion and green pepper; brown in butter.
Add tomatoes; thicken with flour.
Add sugar and salt.
Pour over drained squash.
Place in casserole; cover with grated cheese.
Top with bread crumbs that have been browned in butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail chocolate cupcakes
directions: Put into bowl in order given.
Mix when last item has been added.
Beat well.
Bake in 375°
oven about 20 minutes.

title: russian czar chicken
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350F. Place chicken pieces in glass baking dish. Combine dressing, preserves, and dry onion soup mix, and spoon over chicken. Bake for
1 - 1 1/2 hours uncovered or until done.

title: cream of wheat
directions: Take a nonstick pan with lid.
Keep container on stove; pour oil.
Leave for a few seconds on medium heat.
Put the mustard seed in; let one or two seeds start to pop.
Then put in the onion, chili powder, curry leaves and coriander.
Fry until it turns light brown; put in the tomato, add salt in it and stir.
Leave it for 1 to 2 minutes, then pour in the water.
Add turmeric powder and salt and cover with lid.
Let the water come to boiling for a few seconds; take the lid off and lower the heat.
Start putting the cream of wheat in the water, stirring constantly (and using whole cup).
Then cover with lid; turn off heat.
Let set on stove for a few minutes, then serve with coffee or tea.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix, blending well; stir in sour cream.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with fresh strawberries and grapes.
Yields 3 cups.

title: heaven's golden brunch casserole
directions: Combine baking mix, milk, eggs, butter, mustard, onion powder and nutmeg in blender container or mixing bowl.
Mix until smooth. Stir in ham, cheese, green onions and pineapple.
Spoon into greased 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve at breakfast or with a salad for a light supper.
Try Cheddar cheese instead of Monterey Jack. Serves 8.

title: marie's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain and rinse. Add to all ingredients well. Put in refrigerator.

title: speedy chicken casserole
directions: Heat Campbell's cream of chicken soup and add 1 can of water. Add canned chicken.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add to sauce and serve.
Serves 2.

title: 2 pepper cheese tart
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unfold dough and fit in 9-inch pie or tart pan with removable bottom.
Trim edges of pie dough.
Line the dough with double thickness of aluminum foil pressed against surface.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove foil and continue to bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool; cut peppers into 1/4 strips.
Slice onion in frying pan; heat oil and add peppers and onion with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Cook until softened; remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Shred cheese; combine milk, eggs, cayenne, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Spread cheese in bottom of shell.
Arrange peppers and onion on top and pour milk mixture over.
Bake until custard has set, 45 minutes.
Serve hot or warm.

title: enchiladas suisas
directions: Chop onions and chilies; mince garlic.
Melt butter in saucepan (medium heat).
Add onions; saute until soft (about 2 minutes).
Stir in flour and chicken broth.
Add chilies, garlic and salt to taste.
Add cumin; simmer for 15 minutes to blend flavors.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix and chop and boil in pot for 1 hour.

title: sonia's italian spaghetti
directions: Brown meat with minced onions.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste and mix; bring to a boil.
Add all spices and simmer for at least 1 hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: hush puppies
directions: Cook in fish grease until golden brown.
(If puppy batter is right, it will flip itself in grease.)
Remove and drain; serve with fish.

title: prune-nut cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour sifted with salt, soda and cinnamon, alternately with buttermilk.
Add prunes, raisins and nut meats.
Bake in moderate oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt oleo with onions and celery in skillet.
While this is cooking, chop broccoli.
Add onions and celery along with soups, rice and Velveeta.
Mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until the edges are brown.

title: black-eyed pea spread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Spread mixture on bread slices.

title: german meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, milk and egg; blend well.
Shape into meatballs.
Melt butter in skillet and evenly brown meatballs.
Add beef bouillon, mushrooms and onion; simmer for 30 minutes.
Combine sour cream, flour and caraway seed; stir into broth.
Cook over very low heat until gravy thickens.
Good as appetizers or over noodles for a main dish.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper, then drain.
Add pepperoni and cook 5 minutes on low.
Add sauce and noodles.
Stir together. Place in 13-inch dish.
Place cheese on top and bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: fast broccoli casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in margarine.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cook until bubbly.
Add broccoli and mix.
Add Minute rice, stirring, to mix well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put all together and mix well with mixer.
Put in uncooked pie shell and cook slowly about an hour at 325°.

title: banana split
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Pour into a loaf pan or dish.
Beat 15 minutes at high speed the powdered sugar, eggs and margarine.
Layer on top of crumb crust. Slice a layer of bananas.
Add a layer of crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle the top with cherries and pecans.

title: snickers
directions: Mash very ripe banana and mix remaining ingredients well. Fill Alba package and freeze. Thaw slightly to eat.
Good complete breakfast.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix in bowl sugar and flour; put next 4 ingredients in a pan and let come to a boil, then pour over dry ingredients.
Beat together buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and add.
Put in greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Start frosting when cake is about done and ice soon after taking from oven.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Oil an 8 x 9-inch pan.
Put corn meal and water in the pan to make cornbread.
Cook at 400°.
Let it cool.
Break up the cornbread real fine.
Chop 2 large onions and a whole stalk of celery (not just one stick).
Put in blender with a little water or chicken broth.
Blend until watery.
Pour in big bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir well.
Put enough chicken broth to make the mixture creamy, not soupy.
Bake on high about 30 minutes or until it browns.

title: zuurkool(sauerkraut hotchpotch)
directions: Soak the raisins in a bowl with a bit of wine.
Boil the potatoes and mash them, use a little bit of milk.
Put the sauerkraut in a pan and add the pineapple juice or white wine (not too much, it doesn't need a lot of moisture, like potatoes).
Boil 10 minutes, then drain all the moisture from the sauerkraut and mix with mashed potatoes.
In the meantime, you cut the onion, apple, pineapple and sausage in pieces.
Fry the onion and sausage in the pan; add the raisins, apple, pineapple, some pepper and ginger powder and simmer for 10 minutes.
Drain moisture and add to the sauerkraut and potato mix.
If everything is hot you can eat it right away.
If you want to heat it, put it in the oven for 30 to 40 minutes on 300°F/175° C.

title: pork chops and mushrooms
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Brown on both sides in oil.
Remove chops.
Leave small amount of grease in pan.
Add soup and water. Mix well.
Return chops to pan.
Turn heat very low.
Let simmer for about 1 hour or until tender.

title: beef jerky
directions: Semi-freeze steak and slice with the grain into strips 1/8-inch thick.
Combine all ingredients into large bowl.
Dip meat into mixture and place in shallow glass dish.
Marinate overnight.
Lay strips of marinated meat in single layer on oven rack.
Strips may touch, but not overlap.
Set oven on lowest temperature.
Leave oven door open a crack.
Dry for approximately 4 hours.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and shortening. Beat 1 minute.
Do not overbeat.
Place into 8 x 8-inch square pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: buddig pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until smooth and spreadable.
Separate the slices of ham. Spread each slice of ham with cheese mixture.
Roll and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Chill.

title: fast blueberry pie
directions: Fill baked pie shell with blueberries.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cover with whipped cream.

title: treebeards buttercake
directions: To make the crust generously spray a jellyroll pan with Pam. With an electric mixer, blend dry cake mix, melted butter and egg on low speed until moistened.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes, and pat into bottom and sides of the jellyroll pan, set aside.

title: shrimp spread supreme
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix soup, cream cheese and gelatin in a double boiler.
Heat until cheese melts and is well blended.
Let cool.
Add onions, celery, green pepper, shrimp and mayonnaise to soup mixture.
Blend well.
Grease jello mold and add mixture.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients thoroughly.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt (sifted together), then add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Don't let them get too done.

title: face paints
directions: In a muffin tin, mix cornstarch, water, cold cream and any color in one of the cups.
Use each cup for a different color. Have fun!

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut apples and bananas	into
bite
size pieces.
Drain oranges
and fruit cocktail.
Mix
all
fruit
together.
Pour pudding mix and lemon juice over fruits and mix well. Refrigerate.
(Use enough apples and
bananas to equal one large can size.)

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 10 x 1/2-inch pie pan with Pam. Pour all ingredients in the blender and beat until smooth.
Pour into pie pan and bake until golden brown, about 55 minutes.
Pie forms its own crust as it bakes.

title: very healthy oat muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients. In medium bowl, combine liquids. Pour liquids over dry ingredients; stir until just combined. Spoon into 12 regular or 6 large muffin cups. Bake for about 20 minutes. Cool on a rack.

title: grilled potatoes(serves 6)
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasoning in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in potatoes and onion to coat.
Divide potatoes mixture evenly among 6 (12-inch) square pieces of heavy foil. Seal each end to form packet.
Place foil packets on grill over medium coals.
Grill, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: good home-baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and put in bean pot.
Add water to cover and bake for 2 to 3 hours at low heat (325°).
Stir occasionally and add water, if needed.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut slits through roast and insert in them slivers of garlic and onion.
Put roast in a bowl and pour vinegar over.
Place in refrigerator for 24 to 48 hours.
Then discard vinegar.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients; batter should be fairly thick but thin enough to spread out a little when dropped into hot grease.
Drop by tablespoon into skillet containing 1/4-inch moderately hot grease (bacon drippings work well).
Cook until light brown; turn and lightly brown other side.
Serve while hot with butter.

title: raspberry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla in a mixer bowl until smooth.
Stir in 1/4 cup whipped topping.
Spread in pie shell.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: honey baked ham
directions: Place flour in roasting bag and shake to coat inside surface. Place ham in floured bag.
Combine honey, lemon pepper and rosemary; pour over ham and close bag with twister.
Poke holes in top of bag with fork.
Roast at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until slightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Let stand.

title: baked spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Brown meat balls.
Put in oven dish with meat on top.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: never-fail wacky cake
directions: Stir and mix well the first 5 ingredients by hand.
Make hollow hole in middle and add remaining ingredients.
Stir by hand until everything is wet.
Do not overbeat.
Put in ungreased 9 x 11-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: don's french onion soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, add 2 packages of soup mix and water. Add sliced onions, bouillon cubes, parsley and chives.
Cook to a boil.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with croutons and grated cheese on top.
Put under broiler for 4 minutes or until cheese is lightly brown.

title: corn chowder
directions: In soup pot fry bacon crisp, drain.
Add onion and cook until clear.
To bacon and onion add flour.
Cook on low heat 3 to 4 minutes.
Do not brown flour.
Add chicken broth to flour slowly; stir until smooth.
Add corn, potatoes and milk; heat through.
Do not bring to boil.
It will scorch easily.
Makes 8 portions.

title: eudora sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat for 1 minute after each is added.
Add 1/3 flour (soda mixed in), then 1/2 of sour cream.
Beat well.
Add another 1/3 of sour cream and last 1/3 of flour.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in tube pan for 2 hours at 275°.
(Do not open oven during baking.)

title: house salad
directions: Place in a salad bowl in the order given all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Cut the ripe tomatoes in wedges; place on top of salad.
Serve with oil and vinegar.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: toffee
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar, cinnamon and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly over medium heat until caramel color (15 to 20 minutes).

title: sausage casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into bite-size pieces, then boil until done.
Cut Smokie Links into bite-size pieces, brown and drain. Melt Cheez Whiz and make a sauce adding salt and pepper for seasoning.
Mix all together in a casserole and bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: seafoam cookies or squares
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; stir into creamed mixture alternately with milk (the dough will be stiff).
Press dough into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits over top. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add remaining 1 cup brown sugar and beat until very stiff and glossy.
Spread over dough in pan.
Scatter peanuts evenly over top.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan set on rack, then cut in squares.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Beat egg and sugar well.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a pie shell and put pie shell on top rack.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream.

title: barbecued bird
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate chicken pieces the night before serving.
Refrigerate in plastic bag or well covered bowl. Turn pieces occasionally.
When ready to cook, arrange chicken pieces on grill.
Cook until done.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients together in punch bowl.
Add sherbet to taste.

title: frozen hot day punch
directions: Mix well and pour into small paper cups.
Place a pop stick in the cup and freeze (as many as you want).
Put the rest of the drink mixture in the refrigerator for thirsty times.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to the dry ingredients.
Stir quickly just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add blueberries gently.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: layered potato salad
directions: Layer in order given.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours or longer.

title: mini egg rolls
directions: Brown sausage.
Saute all ingredients together until done. Roll 1 teaspoon mixture in won ton wrappers.
Deep fry until brown.
Serve hot with your favorite sauce.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Cut into a head of red cabbage to form a bowl.
Fill with dip and sprinkle with paprika.
Place cabbage "bowl" in the center of platter and surround with fresh, cut up vegetables.

title: fiesta guacamole dip
directions: In small bowl, combine refried beans and chilies; spread on large serving plate.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning; spoon over bean mixture, spreading evenly.
In small bowl, mash avocados; stir in ReaLime brand and salts; spoon evenly over sour cream mixture.
Cover; chill several hours.
Just before serving, garnish with cheese, tomatoes, green onions and olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Mix in eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour, salt and spices. Fold into creamed mixture. Stir in oats and raisins. Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: one pan beef stew
directions: In large casserole, combine first eight ingredients.
Blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to coat.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bean dip (warm)
directions: Layer 1:
Ground turkey and onion to taste and add taco seasoning.

title: egg crackle
directions: Melt margarine in large cast iron skillet.
Add eggs and bacon bits.
Cook until almost done and then add cheese crackers.
Cook until crackers have soaked up rest of uncooked egg.
This is a must for every Girl Scout camping trip!

title: cherry-coke salad(congealed)
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Bring to rolling boil the can of cherries.
Stir in Knox gelatine mix.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add jello until well dissolved.
Add pineapple (juice and all) and Diet Coke.
Yields 8 servings, counts as 1 fruit and 10 calories.

title: curried tuna salad
directions: Combine rice and peas in a large bowl.
Toss lightly.
Add tuna, celery and scallions.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk
in top of double boiler.
In a large pan, mix all other ingredients.
Stir in melted marshmallows and mix well.
Batter will be very stiff.
Pack in tube cake pan or any other lined pan.
Refrigerate a day or two before serving.

title: nutted wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice in chicken stock.
Boil, then simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Drain and dry.
Chop mint, pecans, onions and mandarin oranges.
Mix olive oil, orange juice, salt and pepper.
Add all ingredients to a bowl and mix.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: antipasto
directions: In a stainless steel pan, combine all ingredients except vegetables.
Bring to a boil; simmer for a few minutes.
Add vegetables to sauce and simmer slowly for about 20 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Cool and then chill.
This keeps for a long time.

title: judy rodger's chilled strawberry soup
directions: Set aside 6 strawberries.
Puree remaining berries in blender with orange juice.
Pour into 4-quart saucepan.
In small bowl, mix tapioca or cornstarch with 4 tablespoons berry mixture.
Add to saucepan with spices.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Cook 1 minute or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Put back into blender.
Add sugar, lemon peel, lemon juice and yogurt; blend well.
Slice reserved berries and fold into soup.
Chill 8 hours.
Add lemon slices.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheeses; add milk and mayonnaise.
Then add Hidden Valley Ranch.
Chill.
Shape into ball.
Roll in nuts or almonds.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix cake mix with other ingredients.
Drop batter on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: shrimp and wild rice
directions: Heat 12-inch skillet over high heat until hot, 2 to 3 minutes. Add 1 tablespoon oil and swirl to coat bottom of pan. Add 1 pound shrimp and cook, stirring occasionally, until just opaque, about 1 minute; transfer to medium bowl. Return pan to heat and repeat process with remaining oil and shrimp. Return empty skillet to medium-low heat; melt 1 tablespoon butter. Add garlic and cook, stirring constantly, until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Off heat, add lemon juice and vermouth. Whisk in remaining 2 tablespoons butter; add parsley and cayenne and season to taste with salt and pepper. Return shrimp and accumulated juices to skillet. Toss to combine; serve immediately.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Place corn in a large greased bowl. Beat eggs in a separate bowl and add crackers and milk.
Mix all ingredients together and fold into baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Put enough flour to make just stiff enough to roll out.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for about 10 minutes. Top with sugar and nutmeg.
Do not brown!

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well. Bake in a tube pan at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom's secret meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ground beef and oatmeal, in blender.
Blend well.
Add to ground beef and oatmeal.
Mix well. Put into greased casserole dish and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: grandmother's meat grinder dip
directions: Grind the olives, pickles, green pepper and onion in meat grinder and let liquid drain off.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended and let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: May want to use as follows:
Melt 1/2 butter in a deep dish. Mix a batter of self-rising flour, sugar, milk and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Pour batter onto melted butter.
Don't stir.
Mix a topping of brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Don't mix.* Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in large muffin cups at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake up what you want and store the remaining in a covered container in refrigerator.
Will keep up to six weeks.
Freeze any extra muffins.

title: panzanella
directions: In bowl put in bread pieces.
Top with onions, tomatoes, cucumber, celery and torn basil leaves.
Dress with an excellent olive oil and add vinegar, salt and pepper to taste.

title: smokey beef ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut ribs into serving size pieces. Arrange in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Bake loosely covered for 45 minutes.
Stir together remaining ingredients. Reserve half of sauce.
Brush ribs lightly with sauce.
Broil for 10 minutes.
Turn ribs; brush with remaining sauce.
Broil for 5 minutes, basting frequently.
Serves 4.

title: tar hill pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter together.
Mix flour, sugars and pecans.
Beat eggs and vanilla together.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool with a dollop of whipped cream on each serving, if desired.

title: broiler snack
directions: Brown ground beef and Italian sausage; drain off grease. Return to frying pan.
Add all spices, Worcestershire sauce and Velveeta cheese that has been shredded.
Keep hot until ready to use.
Use 1 loaf of party rye (sliced).
Cut loaf in half, lay 1/2 slices on cookie sheet.
Put 1 teaspoon of mixture on bread.
Put cookie sheet in freezer overnight.
Put in plastic bag after frozen.
Heat in broiler for snacks.

title: kellogg's all bran bread
directions: Soak All Bran in buttermilk while mixing flour with soda; also mix brown sugar with molasses. Mix all together.
Grease CAN and fill to 3/4 full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Save a large soup can or any smaller cans. Good spread with cream cheese. Yum!

title: potato casserole
directions: Put hash browns in casserole; sprinkle onions on top.
Pour 1/2 melted oleo on top.
Mix together and heat the Cheez Whiz, sour cream and soup; pour over onions and potatoes.
(Can be done in microwave.)
Mix remaining oleo with corn flakes; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken soup and Cheez Whiz over heat until well melted.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: autumn cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and margarine; press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: swiss apple tart
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub margarine in flour.
Add enough water to form a firm dough.
Roll out and line 10-inch tin. Toast nuts under grill; chop and sprinkle over pastry case.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Arrange overlapping in 2 concentric circles over nuts.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of measured sugar. Cook in center of oven for 15 minutes.
Blend cornflower with milk in a basin.
Add rest of sugar and eggs.
Whisk together; add sour cream.
Whisk again and pour over apples.
Return tart to oven for approximately 20 minutes, until mixture has set.

title: aunt mary ann's broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter 'n fudge filled bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Baking Temperature: 300°.
Baking Time: 30 minutes.

title: christmas sausage eggs
directions: Cook sausage over low heat until done and a crumbly consistency.
Drain and set aside.
Cut bread in cubes and place in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Melt butter and pour over bread. Spread sausage over bread and cheese over this.
Combine the remaining ingredients; beat well and pour over the cheese.
Cover and store overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until brown.
Let cool about 10 minutes before cutting into squares. Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° in loaf pan (greased) for about 1 hour or in 2 small loaf pans for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; remove excess fat.
Add sauce.
Place half the noodles in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with half the cottage cheese and half the Mozzarella cheese.
Spread half the meat mixture over.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: microwave caramels
directions: Place butter in large glass bowl and microwave 1 to 2 minutes to melt.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup, salt and sweetened condensed milk.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove plastic wrap (be careful of hot steam).
Stir well.
Put back in microwave 5 to 6 minutes uncovered.
Stir 2 or 3 times.
Remove from microwave.
Add vanilla; stir.
Pour on buttered sheet.
Let cool.
Cut and wrap in squares of waxed paper.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add chicken broth.
Break up noodles and add to broth.
Boil approximately 3 minutes.
Add chopped broccoli and garlic; cook approximately 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and seasoning to taste and cook over low heat until cheese is melted.

title: venison sausage
directions: Chill all meat so it will grind better. Cut venison and pork into 1-inch cubes and spread on a large cookie sheet. Grind beef fat through 3/8-inch plate and spread over the cubed venison and pork. Mix salt and other spices in a tightly covered jar, then sprinkle over meat mixture. Grind entire mixture, using 3/16-inch plate on a grinder, then mix thoroughly with your hands.

title: company broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli 4 minutes or until tender.
Drain and arrange in buttered casserole.
Slice drained water chestnuts.
Add cheese over broccoli.
Combine soup with milk. Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put onions on top and brown approximately 5 minutes.
Don't overcook broccoli.
(A family favorite.)

title: franklin nut cake
directions: Cream butter (margarine will substitute, but not as tasty) and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Add 3 cups flour sifted with baking powder and salt. Add vanilla and lemon flavorings. Mix remaining cup of flour with fruit and nuts and stir into batter, mixing well. Pour into a tube pan that has been greased and lined with greased brown paper (grocery sack is good). Bake in a 250° oven for 3 hours. Let cool in pan. Store in lightly covered container.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well.
Sift flour and baking powder and add alternately with chocolate syrup and flavoring.
Bake in long pan at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat yolks until light and fluffy.
Add condensed milk to yolks.
Fold in lime juice.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Whip cream to soft peaks.
Add sugar and whip until stiff.
Top pie and serve.

title: country-cousin baked beans
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender but not brown. Add sugar, peanut butter, ketchup and mustard.
Blend well.
Add beans and mix well.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with cooked onion rings and snipped parsley, if desired.

title: hash brown and ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in greased extra large pan or 2 medium casserole dishes.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli; cut into bite-size pieces. Combine flowerets, mushrooms, pepper, celery and cauliflower; toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: four layer pie
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over and sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: diabetic peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter with the 2 tablespoons of milk and 2 tablespoons of dry milk until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop on foil or waxed paper in 1-inch balls.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.
Yields 10 cookies.

title: cream of cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage covered in small amount of boiling, salted water until just tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Soften cream cheese.
Blend in cream cheese, celery seed and salt.
Toss lightly with cabbage until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: pie cake
directions: Mix pie filling with cinnamon; set aside.
Put all but nuts and pie filling in large bowl and mix well.
Add nuts and fold in pie filling.
Spoon into greased and floured pan, 13 x 9-inch. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: onion-cheese bread
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons soft type margarine in small skillet.
Add onion and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for ten minutes or until tender.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt, parsley and 2 tablespoons of the sauteed onion in a mixing bowl.
Cut in 1/3 cup of soft type margarine until mixture is like coarse meal. Make depression in center.
Beat egg and milk together and add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan that has been coated with soft type margarine.
Spoon remaining onion over top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes for 8-inch pan or 20 minutes for 9-inch pan, until top is golden brown.
Turn out of pan and quickly turn right side up.
Cut in squares and serve hot.
Makes 9 to 12 squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except margarine.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Dot margarine on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir lightly and continue to bake another 20 minutes.

title: chicken-rice skillet
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook celery in butter until tender.
Stir in water and rice.
Mix.
Bring to boil.
Cover.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in chicken, broccoli and mushrooms.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; mix sugar and flour together.
Stir into margarine.
Stir in milk, eggs and baking powder; mix well.
Stir in corn.
Pour mixture into buttered casserole dish.
Bake until top is golden brown and center is set, about 45 minutes.

title: antipasto spread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; set aside.
Combine all other ingredients, except last three, in saucepan; stir well.
Bring to boil, stirring often.
Remove from heat and immediately pour over vegetables, stirring well.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: baked corn
directions: Warm the milk and corn; mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased casserole.
Place it in a pan of warm water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: black bottoms
directions: Beat cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt. Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Set aside.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Fill midget cups 1/3 full.
On top of mixture, drop 1 teaspoon cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour together in 2-quart saucepan.
Add enough milk to dissolve the sugar mixture, then 2 eggs and mix, add remaining milk.
Cook in saucepan on low heat, stirring constantly until mixture has thickened to pudding consistency. Add vanilla and oleo.
Line bottom of 8 x 8-inch dish with vanilla wafers, then slice bananas on top of wafers, do this alternately until 3 layers of wafers have been used.
Pour on a little more than half of the pudding mixture over the bananas and wafers. Then add layer of bananas, then the last of the pudding mixture. Top with vanilla wafers.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 C. lukewarm water.
Blend lard with sugar, salt, and flour.
Add lukewarm milk and remaining water. Add softened yeast.
Mix until dough is smooth and satiny.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Form into rolls. Place rolls in pan; let rise in a warm place until doubled in size.
Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield 4 1/2 dozen rolls.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
In saucepan, combine caramels and 1/3 cup of evaporated milk.
Use low heat and stir until caramels are melted; set aside.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion; mix well.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: basil pesto
directions: Put everything except oil in food processor.
Pour oil in the feeder hole while pulsing until the oil is all incorporated. Wonderful spread on toasted bread, crusty bread or warm pasta.

title: skillet beef stew in red wine
directions: Run frozen vegetables under hot water or microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes to thaw.
Drain well.

title: swiss sandwich puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Place rye bread slices side by side on cookie sheet.
Spread teaspoon of mixture on each slice.
Top each slice with 1/4 piece of Swiss cheese. Broil for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crustless pecan and coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flour.
Then mix with other ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° in oven for approximately 25 to 30 minutes until light brown.
Do not overcook.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Cool.
Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash avocado.
Add all remaining ingredients, blending until flavors are all mixed.

title: brandie's vidalia onion cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. Melt margarine and saute onions about 10 minutes; cool.
Add sour cream, salt and 1/2 cheese.
Set aside.
In medium bowl, combine all other ingredients, except last 1/2 cheese.
Stir until smooth.

title: eggnog
directions: With an eggbeater, mix eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add vanilla and milk.
Beat until well mixed. Pour into a punch bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: bread pudding
directions: Sprinkle brown sugar over the bottom of a buttered Pyrex baking dish.
Butter slices of bread and dice.
Sprinkle over the brown sugar.
Add raisins.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour over the bread.
Do not stir.
Place the baking dish over simmering water and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
The brown sugar will form a sauce.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix sugar and flour and add to the mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples and cook with juice about 5 minutes. Mix cornstarch with a little water and gently stir into apples; also add cinnamon.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes.
Pour mixture into a 9-inch deep dish pie crust and dot with the butter or margarine. Put top crust on pie.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Pour over the top of 3 small packages strawberry jello in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add the frozen sliced strawberries which are partially thawed, the crushed pineapple (juice and all), 1 cup cold water and the mashed bananas.
Pour half into a 9 x 13-inch dish and put into refrigerator to set up.
When firm, spread with the sour cream. Pour the remaining jello over the top; refrigerate until firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix eggs, water and oil.
Add cake mix.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: raspberry cordial
directions: Will also need a 1 gallon jar.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and sugar in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add oats and peanut butter. Drop onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into walnut-sized balls. Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 12 - 15 minutes. Serve hot. Can be frozen before or after baking.

title: date ball candy
directions: Cook margarine, sugar and dates until dates begin to mush. Cool.
Add 2 cups Rice Krispies, 1 cup nuts and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Make small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add carrots, flour, 4 egg whites (slightly beaten) and cinnamon.
Add pecans.
Fold in 4 egg whites (stiffly beaten).
Pour in ungreased pans and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: party mix
directions: Combine butter, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Pour over combined remaining ingredients. Mix lightly. Spread on ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 jelly roll pan. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Makes approximately 10 cups.

title: lemon pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add extract, egg yolks, lightly beaten, then add flour to which baking powder and salt have been added.
Add fruit and nuts (floured).
Mix thoroughly together. Fold in egg whites beaten stiff, but moist.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour, then reduce heat to 250° for second hour and 15 minutes. Grease and flour pan.

title: peanut butter fudge #2
directions: Mix milk, oleo and sugar; let boil until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until all is melted.
Pour in large pan and cool.

title: chicken casserole 1
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Pull from bone and layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together. Smooth soup mixture evenly over chicken.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box.
Spoon stuffing over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until casserole bubbles.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix cheese and sugar together.
Add thawed strawberries and mashed up bananas.
Fold in Cool Whip and freeze.
Use an 11 x 7-inch dish.
Set out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: graham cracker fluff
directions: Beat egg yolks; add 3/4 cup sugar, milk and vanilla.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over cold water and gelatin.
Pour hot egg mixture over gelatin, cool and set.
Beat egg whites and add to cooled egg mixture together with whipped cream.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar, melted margarine and crackers.
Put into bottom of dish. Save some to sprinkle on top.

title: annie kate squares(chess pie cookies)
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Add brown sugar and stir over low heat until the sugar is dissolved and makes bubbles. Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Stir eggs, one at a time into sugar mixture; mix well.
Add flour and blend well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
The cookies puff during baking but sink down as they cool.
When cool, cut into squares, the inside is rather gooey.

title: mama's cheese dreams
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Gently stir in diced bacon.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Place on buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and browned.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken and onion; cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes or until chicken is browned.
Add mushrooms; cook 1 minute.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and next 4 ingredients; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Serve chicken over toasted, nonfat bread.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in water.
Don't drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cook until it starts to thicken.
Serve.

title: you always ask for more
directions: Line a 9 x 11-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Combine sugar, margarine, 1/2 cup milk, egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla and boil for 5 minutes.
Add graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut to the boiled mixture.
Spread mixture (while warm) over the graham crackers in pan.

title: sausage - pasta supper
directions: Stir-fry the onion, green pepper, mushrooms, vegetables, garlic powder and oregano in the butter or margarine until crisp-tender. Add the kielbasi.
Heat through and stir in the Parmesan cheese. Serve over buttered pasta with additional cheese. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: continental casserole
directions: Fry or microwave 8 slices bacon until crisp.
Crumble and set aside.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In bottom of 2-quart rectangular, greased glass casserole dish, place the croutons.
Sprinkle the cheese over the croutons.
Combine the rest of the ingredients (other than the bacon) and blend well.
Pour over the croutons and cheese.
Sprinkle the bacon over the top.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes until eggs are set.
Quick to prepare.
Great for company breakfasts or brunches.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix all other ingredients in with sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat together butter, brown sugar and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Put in refrigerator 1 1/2 hours or 45 minutes in freezer.

title: sausage-eggplant casserole
directions: Cook
tomatoes and eggplant in salted water until soft. Drain. Mix with remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs. Place
in baking
dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter.
Add the onion and saute until golden.
Add broccoli, garlic, rice and cheese.
In a bowl, combine the eggs and milk.
Add this to the broccoli mixture. Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: fresh apple loaf
directions: Combine cooking oil and sugar. Add well beaten eggs.
Measure and sift together dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients to first mixture. Add vanilla and chopped apples. Bake in well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan for 55 minutes at 300°.

title: february coconut drops
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar and butter together.
Add well beaten egg, milk, vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix well, then mix with dry ingredients except coconut.
After all stirred up, add coconut.
Spoon out 1 teaspoon of cookie dough on greased cookie sheets.
Shape and sprinkle a little coconut on them and put cherries in middle.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter; add milk.
Add sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and okra over rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil; remove and brown okra.
Remove okra and brown onions.
Add to onions the other ingredients and simmer for a few minutes, then add chicken and okra.
Serve over rice.

title: zesty salmon burgers
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Mix well. Shape into 4 patties. In a skillet over medium heat, cook patties in butter until browned, about 6 minutes on each side. Serve on rolls with lettuce. Yields 4 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer hamburger, onions, then rice, then potatoes and put sauce on top, then another layer of hamburger.
Bake until potatoes are tender and hot through and through, at about 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Blend ingredients.
Pour over and toss salad.

title: pork chops a la reese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown pork chops until pink color disappears.
Lay pork chops in a single layer in a rectangular or square pan.
Pour soup (undiluted) over chops.
Cover with foil, shiny side in, and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until tender.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Cheddar cheese.
Place in a 2-quart casserole (greased).
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake for 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sweet pickle juice and set aside.
Mix tomatoes, green pepper, pickles, onion and bacon with mayonnaise/pickle juice combination until blended together.
Layer in a 2 quart bowl or casserole dish with crumbled corn bread, topping with the layer of tomatoes, green pepper, pickles, onion and bacon mix.
Let set about 1/2 hour before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
This salad is especially attractive in a clear glass bowl, so that the alternating layers are visible.
It's a good alternative to potato salad.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and add all of the juice from pineapple.
Fold in cottage cheese, Cool Whip and pineapple. Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Enjoy!

title: potatoes and ham au gratin
directions: Combine
margarine,
flour
and mustard.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.

title: never fail popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and cornstarch.
Bring to medium boil until all sugar is dissolved (about 1 or 2 minutes). Add food coloring and cool until able to handle.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Butter hands and shape into balls.
Keep hands buttered and it won't be sticky.
Wrap in Saran or Baggie to keep fresh.

title: pink fluff
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water and place in refrigerator.
When gelatin begins to congeal, mash with a fork.
Whip cream until stiff.
Stir in nuts.
Fold all together and place in ring mold. Fill center of mold with fresh fruit.

title: rum balls
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water. Remove from heat. Stir in sugar and corn syrup.
Blend in rum. Combine wafers and nuts. Add chocolate and blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls by rolling in sugar. Store in a closed container for several days.

title: johanne's layered potato salad
directions: Layer salad as numbered:

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute hamburger and onion until brown.
Mix mashed potatoes with cottage cheese and beaten egg.
Layer in 2-quart casserole the hamburger, then potato mixture, then cheese until all is used. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can add more cheese on top during last 10 minutes, if you wish.

title: sweet pickle spears
directions: Fourth
Day:
Bring
to
a boil, simmer 1 hour or until change of color.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper chops. Brown in oil. Pour rice into casserole. Arrange browned chops on top. Place a slice of pepper, onion and tomato on each chop. Pour consomm into skillet. Add Italian seasoning. Stir, scraping bottom of frying pan with slotted spoon. Pour over chops. Salt and pepper vegetables. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: boston cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour 1 (9-inch) round cake pan.
Combine ingredients in mixer bowl.
Beat gradually to high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: string beans with cheese
directions: Drain liquid from beans.
Reduce by boiling to 1/4 cup.
Cook eggs until done in simmering (not boiling) water.
Peel and slice in buttered casserole dish. Add beans, butter, cream and seasoning to liquid and bring to a boil.
Add cheese.
Pour over sliced eggs. Cover with bread crumbs. Place in hot oven until crumbs are browned.

title: reese's peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix and press into cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Spread over mixture.
Chill 20 minutes.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured sheet pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: In top of double boiler, melt the chocolate chips over boiling water.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk; remove from heat.
Stir in the rice cereal and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper lined baking sheets.
Chill until firm.
Store at room temperature in a loosely covered container.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: peachy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving juice.
Slice bananas into pineapple juice; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add peach pie filling, marshmallows, mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.
Mix all together.
Stays good until next day.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In a bowl, stir cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually stir in soup.
Add hot sauce, celery and onion.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time, at least four hours.
Serve with crackers, chips or fresh vegetables for dipping.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: stromboli
directions: Chop together the ham, salami and pepperoni.
Let dough rise as directed on package.
Press out on greased cookie sheet into size of large rectangle.
Baste with beaten egg.
Add meat mixture up center of dough lengthwise.
Sprinkle Mozzarella, Cheddar and 3/4 of Parmesan cheese over meat.
Fold over one side of dough into middle, then other side, making sure dough overlaps.
Tuck ends under loaf.
Baste with remaining egg.
Sprinkle with rest of Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cut up chicken and simmer in water with salt for 1 1/2 hours. Remove chicken to cool.
Add noodles and rice to broth and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: In casserole dish, slice a layer of potatoes; add a little salt, a layer of ham and layer of cheese (grated).
Slice oleo over top and repeat layers as many times as desired.
When you have as many layers as desired, pour a little milk over top to give some moisture. Push layers away from sides a little with fork to let milk run down through layers.
Place a lid on and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Drain all fruits.
Combine all ingredients, stirring gently to mix.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix zucchini in blender; mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add lemon juice and beat well.
Add can of milk and mix thoroughly.
Crumble a dozen or so wafers and press into bottom of pie pan.
Add about 12 to 14 whole wafers around edge of pie pan.
Pour mixture over crumbled wafers.
Beat egg whites and add sugar.
Spread this on pie and brown in oven.
Cool and then chill in refrigerator.

title: 7 layer mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Season with salt and pepper and place in 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cut tortillas into 2-inch pieces and place on top of meat.
Drain beans and pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with chopped onion and cover with grated cheese.
Mix together and heat the soup and chili tomatoes.
Pour on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hobo hamburger steaks
directions: Spray aluminum foil with nonstick cooking spray. Put hamburger on foil. Put all ingredients on steak; sprinkle each with Worcestershire sauce. Cook on gas grill for about 30 minutes, turning once. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add mayonnaise to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add soda to cup of warm water and stir slightly.
Pour liquid slowly into dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan and bake at 350° until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Mix in 1/2 package of taco mix.
Add only 1/2 of water as directed on package.
Blend sour cream and cream cheese in a mixer.
Add remaining taco mix; blend well.
Spread cream cheese mixture onto a pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Top with hamburger, cheeses, lettuce, tomatoes and onions. Scoop up with Doritos and enjoy!!

title: cream cheese chewies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 inch pan. In a bowl, combine yellow cake mix, egg, and pecans; dump on top of butter and press down real well. Beat together cream cheese, powdered sugar, and 2 eggs. Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes (or 325° for 1 hour in glass pan). Cut into squares.

title: strawberry shake
directions: Blend in blender the strawberries and bananas with orange juice until creamy.
Add ice cream and blend lightly.

title: grandma jennie haines famous cookies
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: vernelle's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine	and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time. Alternate flour and milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 90 minutes.

title: spiced brown rice salad
directions: In a medium saucepan bring the water to a boil with salt and the 1 teaspoon oil.
Mix in rice and raisins.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 40 to 45 minutes, until rice is just tender.
Mix in peas and let cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, mix vinegar, sugar, cardamom and cloves.
Using a whisk or fork, gradually beat in the 1/3 cup oil until well combined.
Lightly mix in cooled rice, cinnamon stick, cucumber, cashews and onion.
Cover and refrigerate for about 2 hours to blend flavors.
Mix mayonnaise and yogurt until smooth.
Fold into rice mixture.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except fruit pie filling).
Put half of mixture on bottom of small cookie sheet.
Now pour fruit pie filling over dough.
Spread rest of dough mixture over the fruit.
Bake at 350°.

title: ham, corn and potato chowder
directions: Cover potatoes with salted water and cook until tender. Drain.

title: savory bread
directions: Soften the margarine and blend in the herbs.
Spread on sliced French bread. Wrap in foil and bake at 400° on a cookie sheet about 15 minutes.

title: cherry jello
directions: Mix pie filling and water in pan, bring to boil.
Add jello, stir to dissolve. Cool.
Add pineapple including juice, cola, and pecans.
Stir together and pour into 9x13 dish.
Refrigerate.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Brown pork bits with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper in oil in large skillet.
Mix all ingredients, except rice.
Simmer, covered 30 minutes.
Pour barbecue sauce over pork. Bake in warm oven for 30 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and heat for 3 hours on low setting (can also be done in stock pot on low on stove top). Serve hot with cinnamon stick for decoration.
Serves 12.

title: english toffee crackers
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar in saucepan and boil 3 minutes; stir often.

title: old time egg custard
directions: Mix well.
Place in unbaked pie shell and cook at 300° until done.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: In a bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter with mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add 1/2 c. flour, sugar, egg,
baking soda and vanilla.
Beat until combined well.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Shape into balls and place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten by crisscrossing with a fork.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa and oil and melt over low heat in a saucepan.
Add syrup, salt and eggs; stir until well mixed.
Add sugar and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Pour mixture into the pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (the center of the pie will not be firm).

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half and remove yolk.
Mash with fork and add seasoning.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Refill whites of eggs and garnish with a dash of paprika, a sprinkle of parsley or chopped chives.
Other seasonings:
ham and cheese.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Place each ingredient in a large (10 x 12-inch) dish as they are listed from left to right.
Spread evenly.
Refrigerate 8 hours before serving.

title: anna's poor man's cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Dissolve baking soda in the 1/4 cup of hot water.
Add baking soda, water and milk to shortening and sugar; mix.
Add all other dry ingredients and mix well.
By hand, add nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Bake 45 minutes.
Recipe makes 2 large loafs.

title: tuna chowder
directions: Mix salt, flour, Tabasco and water in a large saucepan. Gradually stir in milk and butter.
Drain all oil from only 1 can of tuna.
Add both cans tuna to milk mixture.
Heat over medium heat, stirring frequently, until hot.
Turn off heat, cover pan and let pan remain on burner for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: fish mozzarella
directions: Dip fish in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry fish in oil (lightly).
Remove from oil and let drain.
Place fish in casserole dish.
Pour sauce (Ragu) over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese and sauce are hot.
Serve.

title: butter pecan banana cake
directions: Blend all ingredients and mix for 4 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured stem pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until done. Cool in pan.
A powdered sugar glaze may be added and decorate with sliced bananas, if desired.

title: tortilla appetizers
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together well.
Spread on flour tortillas (about 20 to 24).
Roll and wrap in Saran Wrap; refrigerate.
Slice in 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices.
Serve with picante sauce as a dip.

title: lemon pie
directions: Stir up milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: doo dads
directions: Mix butter and grated Cheddar at room temperature. Add Tabasco. Add flour. Mix like cookie dough. Add water; mix further until ready to roll out. Roll out and cut with round cookie cutter.
Place half pecan on round and fold over, crimping edges. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Will freeze. Heat before serving.

title: beer bread(club member: amanda speed)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients and mix. Do not beat. Pour batter into a loaf or muffin pan, coated with cooking oil and dusted with flour. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in loaf pan or 20 to 25 minutes in muffin pan.
Serve warm.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat yolks until smooth; mix in Eagle Brand milk and blend. Mix in lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell. Refrigerate until firm.
Egg whites can be used as topping, if desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare Stove Top dressing according to directions on package; place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and spread mixture on top of dressing.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chili party dip
directions: Combine salsa, chili and cheese in microwave bowl.
Heat until cheese is melted (about 10 minutes).
Add sour cream.

title: imperial candied pineapple
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar, corn syrup and 1 cup water in heavy skillet.
Over medium heat, cook until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Cook, without stirring, to 232°.
Drop 4 pineapple rings at a time into syrup and simmer slowly 5 minutes. Turn and simmer until translucent, about 7 minutes.
Drain on wire rack.
Repeat until all pineapple slices are candied.
Let stand, uncovered, 24 hours.
Sprinkle all sides with 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Allow to stand 24 more hours, then sprinkle with rest of sugar.
Refrigerate, covered.
Keeps about 2 weeks.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Peel and mash.
Add browned butter and remaining ingredients, mixing after each.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Place 4 marshmallows on top.
Return to oven and brown lightly.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add water.
Stir constantly and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add extract and butter.
Good hot on gingerbread.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place raisins in pan with enough water to cover.
Cook 5 minutes.
Take 5 tablespoons of raisin water and add the 1 level teaspoon of soda and set aside to cool.
Throw remaining raisin water away.

title: potato cakes
directions: Beat egg into potatoes.
Add enough flour to make a medium stiff mixture.
Heat 1/8-inch oil in frypan.
Drop potato mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls into hot fat.
Cook until cakes are puffy and brown on bottom.
Turn and brown the other side.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Add milk to softened ice cream and mix, then add to pudding and mix.
Pour into cooled baked pie shell.
Chill.
Before serving top with Cool Whip and toasted coconut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Refrigerate overnight. Take out.
Refrigerate.
Let sit 1/2 hour.
Roll into ball, then into chopped nuts.
You may use walnuts or pecans.
Spread on Ritz crackers.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix the buttermilk and soda; let stand 3 minutes.
Add sugar and butter.
Cook to 238° over medium heat in a heavy aluminum pan, as it will burn easily.
Stir constantly.
Cool to 125° to 130° without stirring.
Add vanilla and 1 scant cup nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered flat pan.

title: quick and easy squash bake
directions: Cut and boil squash.
Cut up onion and fry.
Drain squash. Mix all ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix corn meal mix, oil, sugar, eggs, flour and milk.
Keep aside.
In a skillet brown ground beef and bell pepper.
Drain.
Pour half of the cornbread mixture in a greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle all the ground beef and peppers on top; then sprinkle the cheese on top of the ground beef.
Pour the rest of the cornbread mixture on top.
Bake at 425° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs,
cream, sugar and vanilla in bowl and mix thoroughly with
mixer.
Pour
into freezer can, add condensed milk and stir
well.
Add
milk
to fill line on can and stir. Makes 4 quarts.
No cooking.

title: crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: easy peanut butter cookies(high fat)
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and egg in bowl thoroughly, blending all sugar into peanut butter. Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet, coated with Pam cooking spray.
Put in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place Kisses or Hugs on top. Let cool 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and onion.
Set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients and toss.
Pour hot meat on mixture.
Toss with 1 small bottle Hidden Valley Ranch dressing or 1 small bottle Thousand Island dressing and 3 tablespoons barbecue sauce.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; stir well and set aside. Combine butter and sugar; cream mixture until light and fluffy. Add egg and mix well; combine banana and buttermilk.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients, stirring only until combined.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Mix lemon juice, sugar and salt into whipped cream. Fold in pineapple, rice and coconut. Chill and serve.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in a large saucepan; add 2 to 3 quarts of water.
Add bouillon to taste.
Cover; bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes, skimming off foam occasionally from top.
Remove chicken; skin, bone and shred back into soup. Bring to boil again and add noodles until done.

title: sunny salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water. Add pineapple juice and water, vinegar and half of the salt. Chill until thick. Add pineapple, nuts and carrots.
Add the other half of the salt.
Mix well with Jell-O and chill.

title: beef gravy
directions: Saut onion in butter in a saucepan until tender. Stir in flour and cook over low heat for a minute or 2. Add warm liquid slowly while quickly stirring. Stir until smooth and cook over low to medium heat until the gravy starts to boil and thicken. You can add more liquid as needed to make the gravy as thick as you wish. Reduce to low and simmer for about 5 minutes to cook out the flour flavor. Taste and add any salt or pepper.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Stir in Butterfingers and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and blend well. Chill dough for 30 minutes.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet and place on wire rack to cool.

title: pineapple apricot muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine flour, cereal, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Add wet ingredients to dry mixture, stirring until just moistened.
Do not overmix.
Spray muffin cups with non-stick spray.
Distribute batter in cups (18).
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.

title: johnny mazette
directions: Preheat casserole at 500° for 10 minutes.
Fry ham, onion, mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce together until ham or Spam is tender.
Pour tomato soup over and add cooked noodles, stirring mixture well.
Cook at 500° for 15 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn off and let stand another 15 minutes. Tastes even better reheated.

title: yummy doughnuts
directions: Cut a hole in the biscuit.
Heat the oil.
Drop the doughnut in hot oil.
Turn it over.
Shake the holes in powdered sugar. Frost the doughnuts with chocolate frosting.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.

title: easy pigs in the blanket
directions: Roll out biscuits flat. Roll hot dog or sausage.
Pinch to seal. Bake for alloted time of biscuits.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix together except for ice cream.
Add this last.
Place candy canes in punch and around punch bowl.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Cook until thick.
Pack in hot jars.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat in a medium saucepan. Add milk, coconut, eggs and sugar and stir until blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool or serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ethel's banana bread
directions: Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Preheat so won't burn before baking.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Pour 1 cup sugar over grated vegetables; let sit a few minutes. Combine 2 teaspoons sugar, mustard seed, vinegar and salad oil. Let come to a boil and pour over the cabbage mixture.
Mix well, cover and put in refrigerator; stir several times.
Let sit in refrigerator 24 hours, then it's ready to serve.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place margarine in oblong dish to melt while oven is preheating at 350°.
Mix flour, sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour into dish over melted margarine.
Add fruit of your choice and bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour hot water over dates and soda; let stand until partly cool, then add sugar and flour.
Bake slowly at 325° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool, then cut into small squares.
Layer cake, Cool Whip and bananas in a glass bowl.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until firm.
Can use cracker crumbs on top.

title: sour cream beef and noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Add beef.
Cook, then drain.
Add onion, pepper and mushrooms with liquid.
Cook until done.
Add Worcestershire sauce, oregano, celery salt and flour.
Stir in sour cream last.
Arrange and alternate layers of noodles and meat mixture in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until heated.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: dear abby's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Form in a baking pan.
Top with catsup or tomato sauce (your choice).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Grind first 3
ingredients and let set overnight in its own juices.
Next day, drain and put pulp in pan;
add chopped celery. Add vinegar
to cover pulp.
Use same amount of sugar as vinegar. Cook
until
tender
and thickened slightly.
Add teaspoon turmeric
before cooking for color.
All measurements are after ground up.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Simmer leeks in butter until tender.
Add water, chicken bouillon cubes, all seasonings and sliced potatoes.
Cook, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Add milk and mashed potatoes.
Stir gently and heat to boiling.

title: 5 hour oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix gently but well. Turn into a 3-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: nut waffles
directions: Brush quick frozen waffles with melted butter or margarine. Sprinkle with coarsely chopped toasted pecans, almonds or walnuts. Set in hot oven just long enough to heat thoroughly at serving time.
Serve hot with honey or syrup with whipped cream or soft vanilla ice cream as a dessert.

title: top of stove meat loaf
directions: *Salsa may be added instead of tomato sauce (minus water).

title: jimmy's oreo ice cream pie
directions: Form crust in oblong pan by crushing Oreos (retain a few) and pouring 1 stick melted butter over cookies.
Spoon ice cream over the crust and spread it out.
Top with toasted, salted pecans. Spread Cool Whip over pecans.
Garnish with crushed Oreos. Freeze.
Delicious plain or topped with hot fudge!
Serves 12.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and chicken separately.
