Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix soup, curry powder, lemon juice, cheese and mayonnaise together.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
If desired, top with a little more grated cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm potato water.
Mix sugar and shortening together; add eggs, yeast, potatoes and flour.
Mix well; cover and let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Take out what you need and make out into rolls and let rise, about 2 hours. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Cover; let stand overnight in refrigerator, then wash and drain.
Mix the next 6 ingredients; bring to boil.
Add the first 4 ingredients.
Let this get hot for about 15 minutes, then put in jars.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil, then simmer an hour.
Can be reheated.

title: fantasy fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough as directed and place in a round pizza pan. Make sure they are close but not touching.
They will cook into each other.
Bake as directed, usually 10 minutes at 350°.
Allow to cool.

title: vidalia onion bake
directions: Mix crackers and melted butter.
Alternate layers of onions, cheese and crackers, ending with crackers.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over the previous mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use any type of fruit to dip.

title: french bread
directions: Put water, sugar and yeast in a large bowl.
Let stand until bubbles appear.
Add all other ingredients.
Knead for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cover and double in size.
This can make two or three loaves.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in dry ingredients, strawberries and nuts.
Pour into loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook pepper, onion and margarine together until tender.
Add next 7 ingredients and mix well. Gently stir in cooked macaroni. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Put in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes
or until thoroughly heated.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Mix the cherries, sugar and flour; cook and cool.
(If cherries are sweetened, sugar is not necessary.)
Crumble the remaining ingredients; put one-half on bottom of pan.
Add cherry mixture and the rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mom's beef stew
directions: Brown meat with flour, salt and pepper in skillet with 2 tablespoons oil; set aside.
In a crock-pot, add vegetables, except corn, and tomato sauce.
Stir in meat and 1 cup water; stir if desired.
Add beef stew mix, salt and pepper.
Last, add corn to fill the crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pour over mixture and let set.

title: applesauce christmas ornaments
directions: Mix together to form dough.
Roll out and cut with Christmas cookie cutters.
If you want to hang this punch a small hole at the top.
Allow to air dry.
This makes your house smell good. You can put a small ribbon at top and hang on tree.

title: spaghetti sauce to can
directions: Simmer all ingredients except oil and paste for 3 hours.
Run through strainer or food processor.
Cook 1 hour longer and add oil and tomato paste.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Can or freeze.
Ready when you need sauce; just add whatever meat you desire.

title: hot pecan dip
directions: Toast pecans, butter and salt in 350° oven approximately 5 -7 minutes and shake every couple of minutes.	Mix rest of ingredients and place in buttered 8 inch pie pan. Arrange toasted pecan on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers. This can be frozen and then baked after thawing.

title: seafood broccoli divan
directions: Place broccoli spears, with flowerets toward outside edge, in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Arrange crab down center of broccoli. Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan; heat on medium for 5 minutes, or until cheeses are melted, stirring often.
Pour sauce over crab.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, egg yolks and water in medium saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Pour into pie shell.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and let stand 30 minutes.
Add eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 325° until firm in the center.

title: orange cookies
directions: Juice and grate the rind of the orange; remove seeds from the juice.
Cream together shortening and sugar replacement.
Add egg, orange juice and grated orange rind, beating until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in sifter and add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Stir to blend.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets 2 to 3-inch (5 to 7 cm) apart.
Bake at 375°F (190°C) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 60 cookies.

title: cake frosting
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and margarine with 3 tablespoons milk in large mixing bowl.
Add more milk if mixture is too thick. (Shortening and margarine may be used as substitutes for each other if necessary.)
Spread on baked, cooled cake.

title: gene's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa until smooth. Add water or milk. Cook until thickened. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Serve with hot biscuits and butter. Serves 2 to 4.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into muffin tins lined with paper muffin cups.	Freeze until firm and store in plastic bags.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet and bake for 5 minutes.
Brown sausage and sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top of sausage. Mix 6 eggs and milk.
Pour slowly on top.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: butter bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse.
Drain well.
In a bowl, mix all ingredients, except Feta cheese.
Cover and chill, then mix crumbled cheese into salad and serve.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno cornbread(makes 8 servings)
directions: Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, jalapenos and grated Cheddar cheese in bowl.
Beat the buttermilk with the egg and melted butter; add to flour mixture.
Stir until just mixed. Pour into greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes, or until firm.

title: baked shrimp cheese puff
directions: Butter bread; make into small cubes.
Put half the bread into a buttered 8 x 3-inch casserole dish; spread with half the shrimp and sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat.
Beat eggs slightly; add seasonings and milk.
Pour mixture over other ingredients and sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: beef tongue
directions: Cover with cold water for 30 minutes. Remove all membranes. Cover with water and cook about 10 minutes.
Drain and put in cold water.
When cold, drain and brown in hot fat.

title: beef tortini
directions: Cook beef and onion; add Prego.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Heat oven to 325°.
Have 13 x 9-inch pan ready.
Mix spinach and cottage cheese in bowl.
Spread 1/3 meat mixture in a pan.
Layer with 1/2 spinach and 1/2 of the remaining meat.
Repeat, ending with the meat.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and mushrooms.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: ham-cheese party rolls
directions: Melt the stick of margarine in pan.
Add the Worcestershire sauce, onion, poppy seed and mustard.
Slice rolls and lay open. Brush inside of rolls with the mixture.
Lay piece of ham on one side and cheese on other side of each roll.
Close biscuits and brush tops with the mixture.
Bake at 325° until the cheese melts (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: honeylulu chicken barbecue
directions: Mix pineapple juice, honey, salt, dry mustard, soy sauce, corn oil and ginger in saucepan.
Simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes; cool.
Brush each piece of chicken with marinade.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Pour rest of marinade over chicken and marinate for 1 hour.
Broil chicken (turning often) for about 50 to 55 minutes or until fork can be inserted into chicken easily (ovens may vary).

title: cranberry-walnut cabbage slaw
directions: In a small bowl, stir together mayonnaise or salad dressing, pickle relish, honey, honey mustard, white or black pepper, salt and celery seed.

title: chewy brownie cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Beat at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat in eggs. Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Empty potatoes and packet of seasoned sauce.
Mix into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat tomatoes (cut up), water and oregano to boiling.
Stir into potatoes. Brown sausage and spread on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in tightly sealed container.
Dip out desired amount and add boiling or hot water. Serve with marshmallows if desired.

title: grecian orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove form oven. Punch about 100 holes in cake when taken up.

title: microwave herbed corn-on-the-cob
directions: You will need 1 large (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients and pour batter in an oven pan after being greased and floured.
Add the fruits on the top and bake it at 375° to 400° for 1/2 hour.
Pierce with a toothpick to check doneness.
Cool for 15 minutes before cutting.

title: complete breakfast muffins
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and add eggs.
Combine and add to egg mixture, the cereals and water.
Combine the flour, soda, salt, and
baking powder.
Add alternately with the milk.
Fold in the raisins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chilled pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse and drain well.
In bowl, toss pasta, mushrooms, carrot, green onion, zucchini, cucumber and tomatoes.
Combine salad oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, sesame oil and hot pepper sauce.
Cover and shake well.
Pour dressing over pasta mixture and toss to coat. Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Garnish with parsley.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Blend
Cool
Whip and lemonade;
add other ingredients. Can be served
in dessert dishes as is or in a graham cracker crust in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: new mexican chicken
directions: Fry chicken in oil and butter until delicate brown.
Remove from pan.
Add salt, pepper and uncooked rice to oil and butter in pan.
Fry until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, tomato paste, tomatoes, mushrooms and water. Add browned chicken; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Melt butter, add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add baby carrots.

title: easy blueberry pie
directions: Pour berries into unbaked pie shell.
Mix sugars, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg together.
Pour over berries.
Dribble lemon juice over berries.
Dot margarine over pie.
Do lattice crust over top.
Place foil around edges.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°; turn oven down to 375°.
Take foil off.
Bake another 45 minutes, until
berries bubble and crust is deep brown.

title: mousaka
directions: *(I used 2 to 3 inch diameter onions & 2 bunches of green onions.) (I added 2 cups chopped celery.)

title: apple streusel(microwave)
directions: Combine in 8-inch square dish apples and brown sugar.
Combine flour mixture with pastry blender.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples.
Microwave at High, 9 to 12 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: yule cake
directions: Combine fruit and nuts in large bowl.
Moisten with brandy. Let stand overnight.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Sift all dry ingredients and mix well.
Beat eggs and vanilla together.
Blend into fruit mixture.
Batter will be stiff.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine pecans and coconut; spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Prepare cake per package directions and pour cake mixture over pecans and coconut.

title: punch with champagne
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
If not drinking, put in cold place.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, celery seed, salt, and mustard and bring to a boil.
Pour boiling dressing over cabbage and onions. Mix well.
Store in air tight container in the refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
This keeps at least a week.

title: truly italian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Pour pasta in large bowl.
Cut artichokes in bite size pieces.
Pour artichokes and juice from jar over pasta.
Add all other ingredients and toss gently.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano, garlic and salt on wax paper.
Dip chicken in butter.
Roll chicken in bread crumbs. Place on ungreased baking dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Add wine and parsley to remaining butter.
Pour over chicken.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: On the dried beef and corned beef, use a food processor to chop very fine. Mix ingredients and form into a ball. Then roll it in dill weed. Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: super quick stir fry
directions: In wok or large skillet, fry meat in a little oil.
After 2 minutes, add the frozen vegetables, keeping the pan hot.
As soon as the ice is off the vegetables, add 2 cups of water.
Use however many packages of Ramen noodles as you need to feed your crew.
(I use 6 packages to feed nine.) Put Ramen in by breaking the dry noodles in fourths.
Add the seasoning packet and stir until the noodles are done.
Add a little more water, if needed.

title: winter fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice cookie dough as directed on package. Arrange slices in bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool.
Peel and slice.
Arrange slices in a greased, 3-quart baking dish.

title: quick chicken gravy
directions: Blend flour and milk and add to soup.
Heat slowly to boiling and cook until thickened.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add 3 to 4 pounds fresh shrimp (cooked, peeled, and deveined).
Refrigerate overnight; stir occasionally.

title: village inn red cake
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add cocoa and food coloring.
Add buttermilk, flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Put soda and vinegar together; mix quick and add to cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pickled cauliflower
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into florets.
Combine with onions and salt.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Combine vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric and red pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add cauliflower and onions.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 7 minutes.
Pack into hot jars.
Process 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: beefy mexican soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in the Hamburger Helper sauce mix, water, chili powder, garlic salt, salt, corn with liquid and tomatoes with liquid; cover and cook 10 minutes longer. Garnish with corn chips if desired.
Yields about 9 cups soup.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use crackers for dipping.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of pan.
Mix mushroom soup, celery soup, rice and milk.
Pour mixture into oleo and put chicken pieces on top.
Cover with Lipton onion soup mix.
Cover with 2 layers of foil and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve on crackers.

title: burger beef soup
directions: Brown hamburger in large saucepan.
Drain.
Add onion and saute.
Add soups, stirring until smooth.
Stir in V-8 and water.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: beans and burger
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Mix other ingredients and then add drained ground chuck.
Put in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish or bean pot.
Put 2 or 3 slices of bacon on top and cook, covered, for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover and brown the bacon.

title: spinach-cheese strata
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 2-quart shallow baking dish. In small skillet, saute onion in butter about 5 minutes or until tender.
Add spinach, heat until spinach is just separated, stirring often.
Drain well.
Toss with bread cubes in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over bread-spinach mixture.
Cut through with a fork to distribute ingredients evenly.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until set and edges are browned.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix together all ingredients and put 2 tubes crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: carrot-pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add enough water to equal 2 cups.
Bring to boil.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved then add pineapple and carrots.
Refrigerate until Jell-O sets.

title: great-grandma sheffer's strawberry pie filling
directions: Wash, cut and sugar berries.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool, then pour berries in.
Put in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Cover with whipped cream before serving.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Layer raw potatoes, sliced onions and carrots.
Sprinkle rice. Add peas and juice and sausage or beef and cover with tomato soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Cover casserole after first hour.
Serves 6.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Put into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple dabble
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together first four ingredients.
Add the next four ingredients to the first, mix thoroughly.
Add the apples, mix well.
Bake for 55 minutes.
May be eaten hot or cold.
May also be frozen for use at a later date.

title: frito pie casserole
directions: Arrange ingredients in layers in casserole dish, topping with generous layer of Fritos.
Hominy may be omitted if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes until done.

title: french lace cookies
directions: Combine the corn syrup, butter and brown sugar in a saucepan. Bring to boiling point.
Remove immediately.
Combine flour and nuts and blend into syrup mixture.
Drop dough onto heavily greased cookie sheets about 4 inches apart to allow for flattening and spreading.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and remove from cookie sheets.
Cookies may be slightly soft when removed from oven.

title: apple dip
directions: Add ingredients together and mix well.
Dip sliced and peeled apples.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Heat margarine and one cup chocolate chips in 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Stir in sugar, flour, vanilla, baking powder, salt and eggs until smooth.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake until center is set, about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine above ingredients.
Cover the bottom of baking dish with crushed Ritz crackers (1 to 1 1/2 cups).
Pour in the chicken mixture and sprinkle with remaining Ritz crackers.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: mom's fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cook only 20 minutes at 350°.
Let set.
Cool before cutting into squares and serve.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs with other ingredients.
Add butter to egg mixture and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Break chicken and pieces of bread up into small pieces.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: beet and orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil and pour hot mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° to 400° until apples are tender.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In a large deep skillet, brown beef, onions, green pepper and garlic with shortening.
Sprinkle with salt and stir in water. Bring mixture to a boil; add spaghetti (broken into 2-inch pieces).
Cook, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Stir in tomatoes and catsup.
Simmer about 10 minutes to blend flavors.

title: jessica's brown chewies
directions: Melt margarine and light brown sugar together.
Let bubble over low heat for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 8-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: candied orange slice cake
directions: Add all flour to chopped dates, orange slices, nuts and coconut.
Let stand in large bowl.
Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs, one at a time.
Stir soda into buttermilk, then add to sugar, egg and shortening mixture.
Add this mixture to the nuts, date, candy and flour mixture.
Stir with a spoon until mixed. Pack into a 10-inch or larger greased tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove from oven when done and while it is still hot, add glaze consisting of one cup orange juice stirred into 2 cups powdered sugar.
Let stand in pan overnight.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make into balls.
Put in uncovered pan.

title: chili rice
directions: Saute rice and onion lightly in butter in a medium saucepan. Add water, bouillon and chilies.
Bring to a boil; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Good with grilled chicken or fish.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter; saute onion and garlic until soft.
Add seasonings and cook 1 minute.
Add broth; boil gently, uncovered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and half and half.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour into blender.
Cover and blend until creamy.
Serve warm or reheat to desired temperature.
Garnish with a dollop of sour cream and sprinkle with chopped chives.

title: carrot pineapple gel
directions: Heat to boiling point pineapple juice, water and salt.
Add lemon jello; stir until dissolved.
Chill and when the jello is about to set add carrots, pineapple and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: tomato and apple casserole
directions: Make alternating layers of apples and tomatoes.
Season with a little salt and nutmeg. Sprinkle sugar on top, then top with bread crumbs.
Dot
with
oleo
and
bake
at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use 1 quart casserole. Serves 4 to 6.

title: sherried onions
directions: In saucepan, simmer whole, peeled onions in salted water until just tender.
Drain and return to pan.
Add butter, sugar, pepper and sherry.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serves 6.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Mix milk and beaten egg and add dry ingredients.
Add melted shortening.
Beat well for only a few seconds.
Fill greased muffin tins about 1/2 or 2/3 full.
Bake in moderate oven (375° to 400°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
May be prepared and refrigerated overnight.
Serve with plenty of butter.

title: good yellow cake
directions: Add ingredients in order. Beat until fluffy. Bake at 350° until done.

title: hanky panky appetizers
directions: Brown meats, then add spices and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Drain.
Put 1 tablespoon mixture on bread slice and broil until brown. Serve hot.

title: microwave apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Mix lightly with apples and lemon juice.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Cut 5 to 6 slits on top of crust.
Microwave on High 8 minutes.
Place in a 425° oven for 15 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: ginger crackles
directions: Measure dry ingredients
together.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs and molasses.
Blend all together.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
They get crisp as they cool.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 13 x 9-inch size pan.
Add flour, nuts and sugar.
Mix and form crust in bottom of pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: anne waller's escalloped pineapple
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir thoroughly and pour into a greased 2-quart baking casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy caramels
directions: Use equal amounts of milk, sugar, molasses and chocolate with a generous piece of butter.
Boil 1/2 hour.
Pour on buttered plate.
Mark off in squares.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in cereals and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet or form into balls.
Cook at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
The dough can be refrigerated for two or three days.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
For parties, mold in small bowl and put in middle of large dish.
Put crackers around it and serve as a dip.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken; salt and pepper to taste. Place chicken pieces in baking dish.
Mix ketchup and Coca-Cola together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake about 1 hour, until chicken is tender and sauce has thickened, turning chicken a couple of times.

title: kathy's cinnamon rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over the 1/4 cup sugar, shortening and salt; stir until dissolved, then let stand until lukewarm.
In small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Beat egg and put into lukewarm mixture, then add yeast mixture.
Blend in 3 1/4 to 3 1/2 cups flour.
Knead with a little flour so it isn't sticky.
Put into a greased bowl, cover with a towel and let rise until double in size.
Punch down and knead, then roll out until it is about a 9 x 13-inch rectangle.
Spread with melted margarine. Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up, then cut into sections 1-inch wide.
Place the sections into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, cover with towel and let rise until double in size. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While the rolls are still warm, spread with the icing.

title: baked pork chops with tomato and rice
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops on both sides.
Place in heavy skillet.
Put 1 teaspoon Minute Rice on each chop.
Place a slice of onion on each chop and pour enough tomato sauce to cover them. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli florets according to package.
Layer broccoli in greased 1 1/2-quart baking pan.
Boil chicken 35 minutes or until tender.
Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; layer on top of chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs (mixed with melted butter) on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes uncovered.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice and mix well.
Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce, marshmallows and pecans.
Fold in cool whip.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 baking dish and freeze until firm. Yield 12 - 16 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put a layer of sliced bananas on bottom of dish, then add a layer of vanilla wafers.
Mix
1 box of pudding mix and 1 can of milk and pour over this.
Repeat this, adding two more layers of bananas and vanilla wafers with pudding on top.
After you finish the layers, add Cool Whip and garnish with vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: judy's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Blend in vanilla, salt and soda.
Add flour, beat well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Roll into balls and press lightly.
Bake at 350° until light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: witches brew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring the mixture to a boil over low heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cover and keep warm until serving time.
Serve in mugs.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: spanish paella
directions: Place carrots, onions and celery in crock-pot.
Add whole chicken.
Top with salt and pepper and liquid (1/2 cup white wine).
Sprinkle basil over top. Cook on high 3 to 4 1/2 hours using 2 cups water.
Remove chicken from broth leaving broth and vegetables in crock-pot.
Bone chicken and cut meat into small pieces.
Return to crock-pot.
In small skillet, over medium heat, fry rice and garlic in olive oil until rice is browned.
Add to crock-pot along with rest of ingredients. Stir together and cook at high 2 to 3 hours.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients and let stand for 10 minutes. Make into 2 large loaves and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off excess grease.
Combine chopped stewed tomatoes, bacon grease and sugar and cook on low for 45 minutes.
Pour tomatoes over hamburger and bake last 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Combine and whip first five ingredients for 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Blend together orange juice, lemonade and bananas.
Mix all ingredients.
Freeze.
Two hours before serving, thaw until slushy.
Pour in 2 (2 liter) bottles of 7-Up.
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together ingredients and jell.
Put in rectangular Tupperware (large) container with lid or similar container.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the first 6 ingredients together.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch dish. Freeze.
Remove from freezer 5 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares.

title: meat, potatoes and tomatoes
directions: Place steak and hot dogs in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sliced potatoes and tomatoes on top and sprinkle with remainder of ingredients.
Add 1 cup water. Cover and bake at 400° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add sugar into a saucepan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cut up cream cheese into small pieces and add to pineapple juice mixture.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water and add to syrup mixture.
Add pineapple, lemon juice and chopped nuts (optional).
Red and/or green cherries can be added for color.
Fold mixture into Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator at least 12 hours.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix ingredients in order given except brandy.
Let simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add brandy and shavings from rind of lemons and oranges.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cake mix.
Melt butter and drizzle over cake.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans in the bottom of a well-greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in mixture and layer in pan.
Combine brown sugar and margarine.
Pour over the dough and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (don't overcook) and invert onto plate.

title: rainbow cookie bars
directions: Melt the margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan in a 350° preheated oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over the margarine.
Pour the milk evenly over the crumbs.
Top with the remaining ingredients. Press down firmly.
Bake for 26 to 31 minutes, or until lightly browned.
After cooling, cut into bars.
Store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: turkey simple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in Reynolds turkey oven bag 2 inches deep.
Add veggies to bag.
Remove neck and giblets from turkey.
Rinse turkey.
Stuff with your favorite stuffing recipe. Brush turkey with oil.
Place in bag.
Close bag.
Tie.
Cut 6-inch slits in top.
Insert thermometer in thick part of thigh.
When thermometer reaches 180°, cook 3 to 4 more hours.
Add 1 extra hour for stuffing.
Let stand in bag 15 minutes.

title: pistachio ice cream pie
directions: Combine crackers and butter; press into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice steak diagonally into 1/8-inch thick strips.
(Steak will slice easier if nearly frozen.)
Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and cook until limp.
Remove from pan.
Add meat to skillet and brown on either side.
Return onion to skillet.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add to meat, cover and cook about 15 minutes. Add green pepper and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper and wine; let cook 5 minutes longer.

title: eggs for a bunch
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer croutons, then ham, then cheese on top.
In blender, whip milk, oleo, eggs and mustard until fluffy.
Pour egg mixture over layers in pan.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: oven pork and cannellini bean stew
directions: Heat oven to 325.
Spray Dutch oven with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat until hot.
Add pork, onion, and garlic; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes or until pork is browned, stirring occasionally.
Add all remaining ingredients except green beans; mix well.
Cover.
Bake covered at 325 for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Uncover and stir in green beans. Cover and bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes or until pork and vegetables are tender.

title: chili
directions: Combine onions, ground beef, salt and chili powder in skillet. Cook on low heat until browned.
Combine tomatoes and beans in saucepan.
Add 3 cups of water to make approximately 8 cups.
Add meat mixture.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour before serving.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix together and marinate meat or chicken overnight.

title: tuna salad plate(60 servings)
directions: Arrangement on plate:
Shreds 4 heads of lettuce.
Slice 14 tomatoes into 60 slices.
Cut 8 large peppers into 60 rings.
Make 60 radish roses.
Place the shredded lettuce on plate first.
Put the tomato slice on the shredded lettuce.
Place an ice cream scoop of tuna salad on top of the tomato.
Put some finely chopped egg around the base of the tuna.
Put a pepper rings on top of the tuna salad.
Garnish with a radish rose.

title: great yeast rolls
directions: Melt shortening and add 1 cup warm water.
Cool to touch.
In a large bowl, mix together all dry ingredients including the yeast.
Add cooled liquid and beaten egg to mixture.
Mix well. Add more flour, if necessary, until you have a good working consistency.
Cover bowl; let rest 10 minutes.
Knead for 1 minute.
Roll dough out to desired thickness.
Cut and place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover; let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; increase to 425° and bake for 10 minutes. Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Mix together dry cake mix, oleo (room temperature), 1/3 cup milk and nuts.
Press 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (metal), greased.
Bake 7 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk.
Smear over baked crust.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over this.
Spread rest of cake mixture on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Refrigerate 30 minutes, then cut into squares.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls.
Arrange in pizza pan, sealing edges. Layer sausage, potatoes, onions, peppers and 1/4 cup cheese over rolls.
Beat eggs with milk in bowl.
Pour over layers.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until set and crust is brown.

title: butter squares
directions: Melt butter and add 1 egg and cake mix.
Press into bottom of oblong cake pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla together and pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fruit salad
directions: Any fruit may be used.
Mix fruit with the pudding.
Chill and eat!

title: paw paw's gumbo
directions: Heat oil.
Add flour; brown on medium heat.
Brown slow; stir often.
Brown until flour is the color of dark chocolate.
Set aside.
This is roux; it will still cook.
Stir often.
In a large heavy pot, add onions, salt, pepper and meat; you may want to use more spices and add 2 1/2 quarts of cold water.
Never put roux in hot water; it turns white.
Let boil on low heat for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Just before serving, you can add file if you desire.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a heavy pan.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat (234°).
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended, pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into serving pieces.
Makes 3 pounds

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve as sandwich on bread or bun, or eat as salad on lettuce.

title: banana upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick of melted oleo and graham cracker crumbs; pat in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat 1 stick oleo, eggs and powdered sugar.
Beat no less than 15 minutes with electric mixer.
Spread over crust.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: toffee topped bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 baking pan and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix together brown sugar and flour.
Using a pastry cutter or 2 knives, cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Remove 1 cup and set aside. To the remaining mixture in a bowl add baking powder and salt. Using a fork, lightly beat in vanilla, milk and egg.
Continue beating until a smooth batter forms.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
In a small mixing bowl, combine the chocolate chips and walnuts.
Fold in the coconut.
Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture over batter.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and coconut and walnuts.
Using a long flat spatula, spread topping evenly over the top of batter.
Bake bars for 35 minutes or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool pan on wire rack. Cool bars completely before serving.
Store in airtight container. Makes 24.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Crust: Remove crescent rolls from can and put all points together in a 10-inch pie plate.

title: coconut brunch bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add sugar, oil and flavoring; blend well.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda together. Alternate with buttermilk.
Fold in coconut and nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: country mushrooms
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and set aside.
Saute mushrooms in remaining grease; add a little butter if needed.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add onion, garlic and bread crumbs.
Saute over high heat for three more minutes, stirring constantly.
Crumble bacon. Add bacon, salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix well.
Serve hot.

title: potato kugel
directions: Add oil, flour, eggs, salt, pepper and Angostura Bitters to grated potatoes and 1 grated medium onion.
Toss together until well mixed.
Then put in a well-greased baking pan and bake at 350° for about one hour or until brown.
Score into squares and serve hot.

title: ham jambalaya
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oil until tender; add bouillon diluted with 1 soup can water, rice and ham.
Cover and cook slowly 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook frozen
broccoli as directed on package and drain. Add all cheese and
stick oleo; let melt.	Crush the Ritz crackers and put
in
melted
oleo.
Pour the broccoli, cheese and oleo in a greased casserole dish.
Put the crackers on top of the casserole.	Bake at
for
20	or 30 minutes until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind apples and cranberries together set in bowl with sugar overnight. Add nuts. Fold in whipped cream. Serve.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to box and add 1/3 cup evaporated milk and 3/4 cup margarine.
Pour half of the batter into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: jalapeno guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
To retain color, place avocado pits in dip and spread mayonnaise over top.
(Remove pits before serving.)
Serve as soon as possible with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer in 9 x 12-inch (3 to 4 inches deep) pan:
lettuce, celery, onion, water chestnuts and frozen peas.
Spread mayonnaise over top like icing.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over mayonnaise, then sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, chop 3 hard-boiled eggs and sprinkle eggs and bacon over top.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: corn bread(very good; easy to make)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix all liquid together. Mix just enough to be moist; don't overmix.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: easy manicotti
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, combine Ricotta, 1/2 cup Mozzarella and parsley flakes; mix well.
Stuff mixture into uncooked manicotti shells.
In large, rectangular baking pan, lightly cover the bottom of pan with sauce.
Line stuffed shells in pan.
Cover shells generously with remainder of sauce.
Lightly sprinkle with Parmesan.
Top heavily with Mozzarella cheese. Cover pan with foil and bake 45 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat blackberries and sugar.
Pour in pan with dough ready. Put dough over berries.
Cook at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cook in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Add the chicken breasts (halved), coating each piece well.
Marinate overnight in covered dish in refrigerator.

title: california punch
directions: Combine the lemon juice, pineapple juice, cherry juice and orange juice concentrate.
Stir until the concentrate melts.
Pour the mixture over ice in a punch bowl.
Pour in ginger ale; stir gently.
Garnish with the maraschino cherries and orange slices. Makes about 25 punch cup or 12 (8 ounce) servings.

title: roasted potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes; cut lengthwise into 8 pieces each. Coat with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Place in ovenproof pan large enough to accommodate all potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in pie pan to make crust.
Sprinkle with cashews and set aside. Saute zucchini lightly in margarine or butter. Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and pinch of dill weed. Beat eggs.
Pour zucchini mixture over cashews in pie pan. Add beaten eggs and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in baking dish. Brown pork chops and lay on rice. Mix mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Pour over pork chops and rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup on top.
Cover and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix cooked sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, margarine, milk and vanilla; put into casserole dish.
Next, for the topping mix brown sugar, nuts and plain flour together; apply on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Melt the butter in a 12 x 16-inch pan.
Mix the milk and eggs thoroughly with a beater.
Add the sugar, salt and flour.
Pour this mixture over the melted butter.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup, jelly or butter.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Boil peppers, vinegar and sugar briskly 3 to 5 minutes.
Add 1 bottle Certo; boil briskly for 2 to 3 minutes.
Set, cool, skim, put in jars and seal.
Add green coloring.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix all together and cook for 30 to 35 minutes.
More water may be added, if desired.

title: jan's tuna and corn casserole
directions: Cut bacon in cubes; brown until crisp.
Add corn and simmer. Drain and flake tuna into corn mixture.
Simmer for 5 or 10 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: peanut fudge(microwave.  power:  high.  time:  11 to 13 minutes)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Microwave at High 11 to 13 minutes.
Stir well at 4 minute intervals.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until melted.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch dish.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut into 1-inch squares to serve.
Yield: 9 dozen 1-inch squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat; drain grease.
Add 3/4 cup water, taco seasoning and kidney beans.
Cook about 10 minutes on medium heat.
Turn off heat and allow to cool.

title: marie cake
directions: Mix together the cheese, sugar and butter and set aside. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup nuts and 1 cup coconut in bottom of pan.
On top of nuts and coconut, spread the cake mix mixture, then spoon the cream cheese mixture on top of cake mix.
Bake approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix together well.
Freeze with ice cream freezer (1 gallon freezer).

title: italian pasta stir-fry
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Drain and keep warm.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat until hot.
Saute garlic for 15 seconds or so.
Add chopped onion and sliced zucchini, stir fry 2-3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes, parsley and seasonings.
Heat 1-2 minutes, stirring gently until heated through.
Remove from heat, stir in pasta.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top before serving.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and 4 cups flour in large bowl.
Add hot water; mix well, then add another cup of flour.
Let rise until double.
Knead and form into rolls.
Roll in butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for about 12 minutes until done.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; brown in skillet on both sides. Layer sliced potatoes in 13x9 baking dish, then sliced onions, top with browned pork chops. Mix mushroom soup and milk together, pour over layered mixture. Bake covered in 375° oven for 45 minutes, or until potatoes are done. Remove cover last 10 minutes to brown top.

title: walk-in cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and pat firmly into a 9 x 13 x 2 cake pan.

title: collards summer
directions: You need a pot large enough for collards and ham.
Put about 1/2 full of water.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours or until tender, then place potatoes in pot and cook for 30 minutes.
Drain and cut up collards.
You may use some bacon drippings on the collards.

title: washington surprise cake
directions: Stir cake mix and pie filling together.
Will be thick. Combine egg, vanilla, oil and nuts.
Add to cake mix.
Blend well. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: quick yeast buns
directions: Measure warm water into a large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar and half the flour; add salt. Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Scrape down sides of bowl; cover. Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 30 minutes. Stir down dough; spoon into 12 large greased muffin cups, filling each 1/2 full.
Again, let rise until dough reaches top of muffin cups, 20 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: granny's dumpling dough
directions: Mix and roll out on a slightly floured board.
Cut in small pieces and drop in broth.
If broth isn't rich enough, butter may be added to taste.
This basic dough may be used with potatoes, tomatoes or, for an economical meal, a can of cream of chicken soup.

title: spicy coffee
directions: Put all in blender; blend to powder.
Careful when you first start blender.
Start slowly, then store in a covered container at room temperature.
To use, put approximately two rounded teaspoons in boiling water.
Enjoy one of mom's favorite drinks.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Combine the chicken, onion, potato chips and almonds; set aside.
Mix the mayonnaise, chicken soup, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Add the chicken mixture; put in a baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Drain tomatoes, save liquid and add water to make 1 1/3 cups. Saute celery, onion, pepper in butter.
Add raw shrimp.
Cook until pink.
Add liquid, tomatoes, sugar and salt, etc.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: chilled pasta salad
directions: Pour dressing over tomatoes, cucumbers, mushrooms and meat. Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Drain.
Combine sour cream, cheese and onion; toss with noodles. Top noodles with vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: pickled red beets
directions: Scrub beets and remove tops.
Cook beets; submerge in water until tender.
Drain and reserve beet juice.
Remove skins and cut beets into desired chunks.
Combine vinegar, juice, sugar and spices.
Bring to boil.
Remove spices.
Add beef chunks and bring to boil.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.
You can freeze this mixture.

title: diet chocolate milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container, blend until smooth and foamy.
Yields 1 serving.

title: walnut pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Blend zwieback crumbs, the 1/4 cup sugar and butter in a medium size bowl.
Press firmly over bottom and up side of a lightly buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: fatal attractions
directions: Melt chocolate squares and shortening, but do not boil. Stir in sugar and allow to cool. Spoon mixture into a bowl; add vanilla and beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture. Beat well. Fold in chocolate chips. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add sugar; mix together.
Add milk and peanut butter; mix well.
Slowly add Cool Whip until all ingredients are well blended.
Pour into prepared pie crust. Freeze.
Remove from freezer before serving, at least 1 hour.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
In large bowl, toss apple slices with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon to cover.
Arrange in pastry shell.
Mix flour and 1/3 cup sugar; cut in margarine until coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: vegetable juice cocktail
directions: Chop celery, reserving leaves.
Combine celery, onions, green peppers and salt in bowl; mix well.
Let stand, covered, for several hours.
Place celery leaves, bay leaves, cloves and cayenne pepper in cheesecloth bag.
Combine with tomatoes and onion mixture in saucepan; mix well.
Cook over low heat until juice from tomatoes runs freely, stirring occasionally.
Discard cheesecloth bag.
Put mixture through food grinder; drain, reserving juice.
Press out about half the pulp.
Combine extracted juice and pulp with lemon juice in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Ladle into 7 hot, sterilized 1-quart jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Seal with 2-piece lids. Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Serve cold.
Yield: 28 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients until thick. Add the last 3 ingredients. Cool. Pour over fresh strawberries in a baked pie shell. Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: tornado cake
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9X 13 pan. Sprinkle pecans and coconut in bottom of pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour over pecans and coconut. Combine butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix well. Drop in dollops over cake batter. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Serve with whipped topping.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits after draining.
Stir in instant lemon pudding. Refrigerate.
If you are making this ahead of time, wait to add banana slices.
Dipping them in lemon juice will help to keep them from turning dark.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar and water. Add cornstarch and cook until thickened. Remove from heat. Add jello, salt, lemon juice and strawberries. Stir until jello dissolves. Put in pie shell and chill.

title: squash pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon french toast with cinnamon syrup
directions: *The preferred is Columbo Sourdough French, but do not bake first.

title: no-fatback greens
directions: Wash and cut greens.
Season to taste.
Cook on medium fire until tender.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger and onions.
Add the ketchup and a little juice.
The longer you simmer it, the better it tastes. I make mine the night before I need it.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, apricots and apple rings.
Keep 3 tablespoons of the juice.
Arrange fruit in baking dish and top (sprinkle) with a mixture of the flour and sugar.
Crush 1 tube of Ritz crackers and sprinkle over fruit.
Cut up the oleo and dot over top.
Sprinkle the 3 tablespoons juice over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix in large mixing bowl.
Put in Cool Whip; stir in pineapple.
Mix in cottage cheese.
Last, stir in pudding.
Make sure all are mixed together.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: garden refrigerator pickles(easy)
directions: Bring the vinegar, salt, coriander and peppercorns to a full boil in a medium saucepan over high heat. Cool completely.

title: chicken noodles-cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions, drain and season to taste.
Mix
cream of mushroom soup and cream of chicken soup. Mix with noodles and chicken chunks.

title: yogurt fruit salad
directions: Combine apple, orange, grapes, bananas, pineapple, kiwi and strawberries in bowl.
Add half the yogurt, mixing well.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Top with remaining yogurt.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator for a few minutes before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook onions in shortening until tender.
Blend in soup and milk.
Stir in tuna and peas, cook noodles.
Pour into baking dish, top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and dash of salt. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside. Peel, core and slice fruit to make 5 to 6 cups.
Place fruit in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with granulated sugar. Sprinkle crumb mixture over all.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad - old south
directions: In large bowl, combine ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: graham cracker cake(once you try this, you'll be hooked)
directions: Will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skin on, peel and dice.
In a bowl mix all ingredients but bacon.
Put in buttered casserole.
Cook, drain and chop bacon and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour or put in a slow cooker.

title: squash casserole
directions: Prepare dressing as directed on package, using only 1 cup of water; set aside.
Put squash and onion in skillet with just enough water to steam nearly done.
Salt and pepper.
Drain.
Mix sour cream, soup and pimientos.

title: linda's famous peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter pan and set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, milk, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 7 to 10 minutes, stirring all the time.
Test until it forms soft ball.
Take off heat; beat in chocolate chips, vanilla, peanut butter and nuts.
Pour into pan; let cool before cutting.
Try me.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare lime gelatin as directed.
Chill until slightly firm, then fold in pineapple.
Pour in 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Add mayonnaise to softened cheese.
Mix well until blended.
Add nuts and spread over molded jello layer.
Chill until firm. Prepare strawberry gelatin and add cranberry sauce.
Pour this over cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut in squares.

title: pork with peanut sauce
directions: In a shallow glass dish, mix 2 tablespoons of the soy sauce, 4 tablespoons of the lemon juice, oil, garlic and salt.
Add pork and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain marinade from meat; reserve marinade.

title: rocky road brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9-inch pie plate with cooking spray. Combine flour and salt, set aside. Melt chocolate in a double boiler over hot water. Remove from heat and mix in butter and sugar. Add flour and salt mixture, vanilla and egg to chocolate mixture and mix until smooth. Spread batter in pie plate and bake until set, about 15 minutes. Sprinkle topping mixture over brownie layer. Bake for 10 minutes or until pizza pulls away from sides of plate. Cool and cut into wedges. Makes 8 servings.

title: no bake rice krispy treats
directions: Mix corn syrup and peanut butter together, then add the Rice Krispies.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach.
Place between paper towels and squeeze out water.
Mix all ingredients and serve with crackers or chips.

title: beef bristo potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes in foil for
1 hour at 400°.
Melt butter and oil in heavy skillet; add beef and brown.
Add onion salt, garlic and parsley.
Combine tomato paste and seasonings.
Add to beef and simmer for
minutes.
Open
potatoes and scoop out most of potato;
add
to
beef
mixture
and toss lightly. Fill potato shells and serve with sour cream.

title: pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Whip the egg whites and add 6 level tablespoonfuls of sugar while beating.
Place this mixture in the refrigerator until the rest of the cake is mixed.
Cream the butter, gradually, and the rest of the sugar and whip until light. Add egg yolks about 2 at a time, beaten well after each addition. Add flour and cream alternately.
Whip until the mixture is as light as possible, and it takes a few minutes on the electric mixer or longer by hand.
(I use the electric mixer on low speed for 10 minutes.)
Then with mixer on low speed, whip in egg whites only long enough to mix well.
Pour batter into greased tube pan 10 inches in diameter and 4 inches deep.
Bake as you would an angel food.
Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.
This cake is supposed to fall which makes it better.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Clean and cut strawberries with 1/4 cup sugar and set aside. Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and salt.
Boil until thick.
Add 1 package of strawberry jello less 1 tablespoon.
Add a few drops of red food coloring, if desired.
Pour 1/2 mixture into baked pie shell; add strawberries.
Pour remaining mixture over strawberries.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream, if desired.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with melted oleo.
Mix well and pour in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Combine softened oleo with brown sugar, flour and coconut.
Mix well and sprinkle over potato mixture and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Wash and prepare peppers, making just the smallest hole in the stem end of pepper.
Stuff with mixture of rice and uncooked ground chuck.
Place in a Dutch oven; cook on top of stove.
Cover peppers with tomatoes.
Be sure to keep sauce over peppers all the time they are cooking.
Cooking time is approximately 1 hour.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients; put in pie shell and bake at 350° until toothpick is clean, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream and warm hot fudge.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: With 1 inch of boiling water in saucepan, boil onions and potatoes with 2 teaspoons salt, covered, for 5 minutes; drain. Cook flour, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, paprika, milk and cheese. Cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Arrange potatoes and onions in greased 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Follow with parsley, sauce, potatoes and onions; repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.

title: peanutty sweet potatoes
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven, top with marshmallows.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan with egg, flour, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Let mixture cool.
Pour over fruit and marshmallows.
Before serving, fold in Cool Whip and peanuts.

title: sand cups
directions: Mix pudding and milk until well blended. Let stand 5 min. Stir in Cool Whip and 1\2 of crushed cookies into each cup.
Fill 3\4 cup with pudding and top with remaining crushed cookies. Decorate with umbrellas, gummy sea shells, shark bites, etc.

title: five flavored cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Stir in flavorings and mix well afterward.
Bake in a tube cake pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until well done.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour or until done.
When cool, top with Caramel Frosting, if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain.
Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Mix squash, onion, soup, egg, and Stove Top stuffing and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° about 30 to 35 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle rest of cheese on top and let cheese melt.

title: nut roll
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add cream. Cream together butter, shortening, and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and salt together, add alternating with yeast mixture. Beat well until dough no longer sticks to hands. Cover with wax paper and refrigerate overnight. Cut dough into four parts. Roll out each part on floured board until thin. Spread with favorite nut filling or poppy seed filling. Roll up like jelly roll. Place on greased baking sheet and let rise for 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Makes four nut rolls.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: valley salad
directions: Mix well and boil for 20 minutes. Less vinegar will do. I add 1 tablespoon celery seed to mine. Seal while hot.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place chicken on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover 1/2 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together and add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in raisins and nuts last.
Spoon batter into well-greased bread tin, 9 x 5 1/2-inch size.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is really a not too sweet cake.
It is good with cream cheese.

title: black forest pie
directions: Beat cream cheese on medium speed until smooth; gradually add milk.
Add pudding mix; beat at low speed for about 1 minute. Spread into pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Just before serving, spoon cherry pie filling over pie.
Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: mom's apple dumplings
directions: Melt in baking dish:
1 cup sugar, margarine and water.
Mix together 1 cup sugar, apples, apple spice mix and cinnamon or nutmeg, etc.
Roll out biscuits separately.
Put apple mixture in center.
Fold and pinch tops together.
Place in baking dish in melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes. While cooking, spoon the juice and butter in bottom of pan over dumplings occasionally.
June apples are good.

title: cheese cake
directions: Blend cheese, 1/2 vanilla and 2/3 cup sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in blender or high speed with mixer.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Place rack below center of oven.
Cool 20 minutes.
Blend vanilla, sugar and sour cream together (do not use blender or mixer).
Pour in center of pie at least 1-inch from sides.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: pineapple rice pudding
directions: Add rice to boiling water; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add pineapple and milk; cook 15 minutes over low heat. Stir in raisins, sugar and cinnamon.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados.
Add diced tomatoes, chopped onions, lemon juice, picante sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: tropical upside-down salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Cut each pineapple slice into 3 equal pieces; cut each cherry in half.
Place 2 pineapple pieces and 1 cherry half in bottom of each of six 6 ounce custard cups.
Bring pineapple liquid to a boil.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved. Let cool.
Add milk and mayonnaise; blend well, using rotary beater.
Chill until partially congealed.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon about 1/2 cup gelatin mixture into each cup.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Invert to serve.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar 5 minutes on high speed.
Add condensed milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into freezer; fill with milk.
Add vanilla.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm.
In a small bowl, sprinkle yeast over water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir yeast mixture into lukewarm milk mixture.
Add 2 1/4 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour. Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; brush with margarine.
Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 hour.
Punch down and turn out on lightly floured board.

title: grilled london broil
directions: Combine vinegar, sauce, oil, garlic and pepper in a large shallow container, mixing well.
Add steak.
Turn and coat each side.
Cover and refrigerate 12 hours.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving marinade.
Grill, covered, over medium-hot coals, 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until desired degree of doneness.
Baste occasionally with marinade.
Remove from grill and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt, if desired.
Cut into thin slices.
London Broil is made using top round or flank steak.
Flank steak will cook slightly faster.
Yields 10 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; pour off grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and let simmer.
Cook noodles.
Mix cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper. Drain noodles.
Put hamburger in bottom.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese mixture, cheese and noodles.
Put hamburger on top.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: kielbasa bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, saute vegetables slightly; add water and simmer 10 minutes; or until tender.
Add kielbasa and bean soup lastly.
Heat.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt the chocolate in the boiling water.
Cream together butter and sugar; beat in the egg yolks, one at a time.
Add the melted chocolate and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add this to the chocolate mixture alternating with the buttermilk.
Do not cream.
Beat the egg whites and fold in very gently.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour in 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool and frost with favorite icing.
My favorite is Seven Minute Icing.

title: roast turkey with popcorn dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix salt, pepper and onion.
Rub turkey inside and out with butter or margarine.
Dust inside and out with salt mixture.
Bake 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Take out of oven; put in the unpopped popcorn.
Sew up tight.
Put back in oven at highest heat.
Go sit down and relax until the popping stops and bursts the stitches.
The dressing is done.
Remove from the stove with broom and shovel.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If too dry, add a little broth, 1/3 to 1/2 cup.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham patties with sour cream
directions: Combine ham with remaining ingredients, except sour cream. Shape mixture in 6 small or 4 large patties.
Brown slowly on both sides in a small amount of hot fat.
Heat sour cream just until hot.
Serve with patties.
Trim green onion tops or chives.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Let them marinate overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, then turn oven to 450° and cook for 15 more minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: spinach dip
directions: Wash spinach.
Boil 4 minutes in 1-inch of water in a heavy pan.
Drain, cool and chop finely.
Fold in remaining ingredients (except bread).
Chill 8 hours.
Hollow out the French bread and fill with dip.
Serve with crackers and sliced bread.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Let sugar and oil come to boil.
Add dill weed.
Let cool. Add pimento for color if desired.
Pour over vegetables.

title: grandma's chili sauce
directions: Boil celery, onions and green pepper in small amount of water for 1/2 hour. Add tomatoes. Bring to a boil. Let bubble for 20 minutes. Add sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Continue to boil for 5 minutes. Put in jars and seal.

title: melt-in-your-mouth blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/4 c. sugar until they form stiff peaks; set aside.
Cream butter.
Add salt, vanilla and sugar, beat well.
Add egg yolks and beat until light and creamy.
Add flour and baking powder, then milk.
Fold in egg whites, then blueberries.
Pour into greased 8 inch square pan.
Sprinkle top lightly with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes.
This cake freezes well.

title: beans, bacon and cheese
directions: Melt cheese whiz in a large pan.
Drain beans and add to pan. Cut bacon into squares and fry until brown and crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels then add to pan.
Mix all together and serve hot.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together until smooth.
Next, fold in berries.
Make Dream Whip and mix all ingredients together.
Put into baked pie shell.
Garnish with berries.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: After cabbage is shredded, add all ingredients for dressing and apply to cabbage.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix up and pour into 12 muffin tins, greased if not Teflon. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Watch; do not overdo.

title: orange date bread(sugar-free)
directions: Cream butter; add eggs, juice and water.
Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to butter mixture, beating thoroughly.
Add nuts and dates; mix well.
Pour into 2 small, greased loaf pans and let set 20 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quesadillas
directions: Mix beef and picante sauce.
Heat in microwave for about 5 minutes.
On medium heat, heat skillet or griddle.
Lay one tortilla shell in hand and fill half of shell with 1/4 meat mixture.
Sprinkle with both cheeses and a couple slices of peppers.
Fold top of shell over filling and heat on griddle until pretty and brown.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, etc. if desired.

title: unbaked cheesecake
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Cool.
Cream large package cream cheese with 1 cup sugar.
Add Jell-O mixture.
Add Carnation milk.
Beat slowly with electric mixer until thick.
Add drained pineapple.
Pour into a 13 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish that has been lined with graham cracker or vanilla wafer crust.
Chill overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a long pan with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until clear and thick.
Cool.
Fold in the other half of sliced berries.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Butter a baking sheet 15 1/2 x 2-inches.
Keep warm.
In 2-quart casserole, mix nuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Microwave on High 4 minutes; stir and microwave 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Syrup will be hot and peanuts lightly browned.
Stir in soda until lightly colored and foamy.
Pour onto warm cookie sheet.
Don't spread.
Allow to set until cool enough to handle.
Stretch to make thinner, if desired. Cool and break into pieces.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, melted butter, vanilla, syrup, salt and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add pecan halves.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, then lower heat to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, egg, lard (can substitute thick sour cream), flour, baking soda, pepper, cloves, nutmeg and salt. Knead, roll out in a roll and put in refrigerator.
Chill.
Slice what you want to bake.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
In a measuring cup, measure orange juice and add water, if necessary, to equal 3/4 cup.
Add grated orange rind and oil and stir in beaten egg.
Pour this mixture into the dry ingredients.
Mix just enough to dampen. Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan. Bake 50 minutes to an hour.
Remove from pan to cool.
Store overnight for easy slicing.

title: small cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and make 3 wells in mixture. Put vinegar in one well and melted (but not hot) butter in remaining wells.
Then pour 1 cup cold water over all and beat well.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sundae pie
directions: Line pie pan with foil and press graham cracker crust into pan.
In a saucepan, cook marshmallows, chocolate chips, salt and milk until blended, about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Alternate layers of ice cream and fudge sauce in pie pan.
Freeze.
Serve with topping.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: In a saucepan, stir in flour, cinnamon and salt.
Gradually stir in thawed apple juice.
Heat on low until thickened. Coat apples with the thickened juice and fill the pie shell.
Dot with margarine. Adjust top crust and sprinkle with water and nutmeg. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes, longer if necessary.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add flavoring last.
In a Bundt pan, add a layer of batter, then sprinkle with a mixture of 1/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon, then add a layer of batter, then sprinkle with sugar mixture, ending with batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand for 8 minutes, then remove from pan.
Glaze.

title: ella's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer pudding mixture, bananas and vanilla wafers in a serving bowl.
Repeat layers.
Chill, serve and enjoy.

title: baked quail in sherry sauce
directions: Soak quail overnight in 3 cups milk.
Salt and pepper birds and roll in flour.
Brown quail in butter, then place in a baking dish.
Pour off half of drippings.
Saute onion and bell pepper in same skillet.
Add soup, wine and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir well and pour over quail.
Cover and bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: russian salad
directions: Mix boiling water, jello, cream cheese and marshmallows together and cool.	Add other ingredients; chill until firm.
May add cherries if desired.

title: mrs. pusey's white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over the boiling water in a double boiler. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and add to first mixture alternately with buttermilk in 4 to 5 additions.
Don't overbeat.
Stir in coconut flakes and chopped nuts.
Turn batter into three greased layer cake pans. Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.
Remove from oven and cool at least 10 minutes.
Turn onto rack to cool.

title: rolled meat loaf
directions: Roll out meat to 1/2-inch thickness.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add layer of onion, tomato, bell pepper and cheese.
Roll meat like a jelly roll.
Place in dish, seam side down.
Pour mushroom soup over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Boil dates, raisins, prunes and water until soft; about 6 minutes.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo, combine all ingredients and stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: elaine's peanut butter "pie"
directions: Bake pie shells according to package.
In bowl, mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar until creamed.
Add peanut butter and Cool Whip; stir until creamy.
Pour into baked pie shells. Chill and serve.

title: round steak in foil
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Cut heavy-duty foil into 5 pieces, 15 inches long.
Place one piece of steak on each piece of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Roll foil, sealing edges well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or grill for 45 minutes.
Yields 5 servings.

title: mama's dressing for potato salad
directions: Beat the eggs in top of double boiler.
Add the flour, sugar and dry mustard; blend well.
Heat the vinegar and butter.
Add slowly to egg mixture, stirring until smooth.
Cook in double boiler until thickened.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Return to heat until it boils.
Cool and serve over potato salad.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix grated cheese and sausage well. Gradually mix in biscuit mix. Combine well to form a dough.
Make a slit in each pepper and remove the seeds and stem.
Place a small amount of Monterey Jack cheese in the middle of each pepper and close it.
Make a flat pancake from the dough mixture and wrap around each pepper.
Roll it in your hands to form egg shape.
Roll each egg in Shake 'n Bake, then egg, then Shake 'n Bake again.
The eggs may now be frozen or baked.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. They will be soft after baking but will firm as they cool. They are best served warm.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popped corn and nuts in large roasting pan.
Heat brown sugar, margarine and syrup; boil 5 minutes.
Pour over corn and nuts.
Stir well.
Bake about 50 minutes at 250°, stirring occasionally.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell and chill.
Spread ice cream evenly over cold pie shell and freeze.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Turn into casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Sprinkle chow mein noodles over top the last 20 minutes of baking time.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: applesauce-spice bars
