directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Heat oven to 350°.
Beat applesauce, sugar, oil and eggs on medium speed for 1 minute. Stir in baking mix, pumpkin pie spice and nuts.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake for about 25 minutes; cool.
Frost with vanilla or chocolate frosting and cut into bars about 3 x 1-inch.

title: orange salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and chill slightly.

title: union mills cole slaw
directions: Mix chopped pepper, onion and celery.
Let stand while cutting cabbage.
Add pinch of celery seed, pinch of mustard seed, sugar and salt to vinegar and mix well.
Mix all ingredients.
Must stand to season overnight in refrigerator.
Stir again before serving.
It makes its own brine.

title: gina's banana ice cream
directions: Beat eggs vigorously for 3 minutes.
Put into ice cream maker; add remaining ingredients and stir with long handled spoon.
Add whole milk to the fill line.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: persian baklava
directions: Place 3 or 4 sheets of fillo (or "fila") pastry evenly over the bottom of a well-greased oblong cake pan, brushing each sheet on both sides with melted butter before putting another sheet on top.
Thoroughly mix together almonds, cardamom and sugar.
Spread evenly over pastry sheets.
Place 3 or 4 sheets buttered fillo on top of nut/sugar mixture.
Cut into 2 x 2-inch squares or diamonds.

title: pizza on rye
directions: Cook and crumble sausage and beef; drain.
Add rest of ingredients except bread
Heat until cheese melts. Spread on rye bread.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
This is also good with a slice of jalapeno pepper on each.

title: percolator punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, cranberry juice cocktail, water and brown sugar.
Put rest of ingredients in brew basket of urn style percolator.
Add juice mix to urn or percolator and brew like coffee.

title: deep fried turkey
directions: You will need an outdoor flame cooker, propane, deep frying pot and thermometer.

title: pineapple cheese
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Put pineapple in dish.
Dice cheese and put over pineapple.
Mix flour and sugar and sprinkle over pineapple and cheese.
Pour juice over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lazy day dessert bars
directions: Combine instant oatmeal and butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan; mix well.
Press evenly into bottom of pan.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts over oatmeal base; sprinkle with coconut.
Pour milk over coconut.
Bake in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for about 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars while a little warm.

title: venison stir-fry
directions: Boil venison
until
tender.
Drain
off
water and cut into small pieces
or
strips.
Put
into a frying pan or iron skillet with
deep	sides.	Cut
up
tomatoes,
onion and bell pepper. Add butter	and stir on high to melt the butter.
Add salt and pepper
to taste.
Keep stirring to prevent burning. Turn stove on medium.
Cover and let simmer for about 20 or 30 minutes or until done.

title: farmer's chicken salad
directions: Add and gently toss chicken, oil, orange juice and vinegar. Combine remaining ingredients and refrigerate several hours. Serves 12.

title: pepper jelly
directions: *Use sweet red peppers and red food coloring if you prefer red color.

title: zellwood corn pudding
directions: Scrape corn from the cob and combine with other ingredients. Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 325° for one hour or until set.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Cook chicken in small amount of salted water until tender. Remove skin and bones from meat.
Add cream cheese to chopped chicken and mix well.
Put heaping tablespoon of mixture on each crescent roll.
Wrap dough around filling.
Roll in melted butter and crumbs.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 8 rolls.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Bring to a boil in a large pan the water and sugar.
Add cranberries.
Cook just until berries begin to pop open.
Put into a large bowl the Jell-O.
Add cooked cranberries, pineapple, celery and nuts.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: berry good punch
directions: Mix ginger ale and juice or punch in large bowl.
Add frozen berries and serve.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Boil chicken until tender; cut in bite size pieces.
Add tomatoes, mushroom soup and chicken soup to onions.
Stir until hot.
Add chicken to mixture.
Grease casserole dish with half the tortilla shells torn in pieces.
Pour half of chicken mixture on top of shells.
Top with cheese and another layer of tortilla shells.
Then chicken mixture and top with rest of cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and golden.

title: mexican luncheon(serves 6)
directions: Brown sausage in skillet with onion and green pepper.
Add noodles, milk, sour cream, tomatoes, chili pepper and salt. Layer this with cheese.

title: squash fritters(very good)
directions: Mix well all ingredients. Make into patties and fry.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine blueberries, sugar, flour, lemon juice, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Spoon into pie crust and dot with butter.
Cover with 2nd pie crust and flute edges.
Cut slits in top.
Bake for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Mix all other ingredients except stuffing mix and butter.
Place broccoli in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour over ingredients over broccoli.
Combine stuffing mix and melted butter.
Sprinkle around edge of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. (This is better if prepared and refrigerated overnight and baked next day.)

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and melted butter; put on bottom of greased pan.
(It will be sticky.)
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of cake mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle small amount of powdered sugar on top of cooled cake.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in a large bowl.
In a saucepan, add margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Pour over flour and sugar.
Stir well.
Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Batter will be thin.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Start frosting as soon as cake is in oven.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Drop by tablespoons onto batter.
Cut through batter with knife or spatula several times for marbled effect.
Sprinkle with additional chocolate chips and chopped nuts, if desired.
Bake until the cake springs back when touched lightly in center or when wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line a 9 x 13
x 2-inch glass dish with vanilla wafers. Slice bananas over the top of wafers.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to directions of box.
Fold into the pudding mixture the Eagle Brand and Cool
Whip.
Spread
this mixture over the wafers and bananas.
Chill.
Serves about 8.

title: white hot rice
directions: Mix cooked rice, sour cream, cheese, jalapenos and salt and pepper together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Heat in oven at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Trim crusts from bread. Arrange half the bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish coated with butter or cooking spray. Combine milk, 6 eggs, half and half and 1/2 cup sugar in a large bowl, stirring with a whisk. Pour half of milk mixture over bread in dish. Combine 2 eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and cream cheeses in a food processor or blender; process until smooth. Pour cream cheese mixture over moist bread in dish. Top with remaining bread; pour remaining milk mixture over bread. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: fried quail with cracked black pepper
directions: Rinse the quail in water, then place in a shallow pan and cover with buttermilk.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Coat
chicken
pieces with oleo melted in pan.	Mix all ingredients together except butter (oleo) and pour into baking dish
or
pan.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° to 400°.

title: brownie cake and frosting
directions: Bring cocoa, water and margarine to a boil in saucepan. Combine flour, sugar and soda; mix well into the hot mixture. Beat buttermilk or sour milk, eggs and vanilla well and add to mixture.
Pour into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ice while cake is still warm.

title: pineapple casserole(good with ham)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, bread and pineapple; mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zesty potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until done; drain, cool, then cut into cubes. In large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, parsley, salt and pepper. Mix until smooth. Stir in potatoes, bacon, eggs and onions.
Cover and chill for up to 24 hours. Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet 'n sour sauce
directions: In large saucepan, combine pineapple juice, vinegar, cornstarch, brown sugar and soy sauce.
Stir until well mixed. Add pineapple and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Use whenever Sweet 'N Sour Sauce is needed.

title: chicken mystery
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have ready a 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter in a medium size heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth and frothy.
Let mixture bubble about 3 minutes, stirring often.
Gradually stir in half and half. Increase heat to medium and simmer, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Stir in salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
Put remaining ingredients except sauce and mayonnaise in baking dish. Stir in mayonnaise, then white sauce. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 regular servings.

title: grace's okra
directions: Slice okra about 1/2 inch thick.
Roll in meal and salt.
Fry in canola oil until light brown and crispy.

title: ham swiss cheese dinner  roll appetizers
directions: Soften butter.
Add ingredients except ham, cheese, rolls. Take rolls out of package and slice through the middle and open like a sandwich.
DO NOT pull rolls apart.
Spread the margarine mixture on the rolls.
Place 1 slice thickness of ham on the rolls and 1 slice thickness of cheese, overlapping to a minimum.
Place top of roll over bottom and replace in tray.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to heat.
Heat in 400° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Quickly add liquid ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Bake in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour (or until toothpick comes out clean).
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pans.
Tastes better the next day.
(Great Fall treat.)

title: walnut carrot cake
directions: Grease 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans well.
Resift flour with baking powder and salt.
Combine sugar, eggs, oil and spices. Beat at high speed until light and well mixed.
Add half of flour mixture.
Stir in milk, then remaining flour.
Stir in carrots and chopped walnuts.
Divide batter evenly in pans.

title: layer dinner
directions: Mix in order.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
You do not cook the hamburger first, crumble it in raw.

title: chicken rice salad
directions: Combine.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or hot bread for a meal. Serves 12.

title: paradise salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, drained from can and add juice from cherries.
Place in refrigerator while other ingredients are prepared.
Cut pineapple in small pieces and cherries in halves.
Add marshmallows and chopped pecans.
When gelatin thickens, whip with rotary beater until fluffy.
Whip cream and fold into other ingredients.
Mold as desired.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bone and cut in small pieces.
Cook noodles in same water as the chicken.
Drain noodles and add everything but cayenne pepper.
Put in 9 x 12-inch dish and sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mushroom-cheese casserole
directions: Spread butter on one side of bread slices.
Place bread slices, butter side down, in a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan with butter. Beat all ingredients. Bake 18 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer. Serve with syrup or jam.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into ball, then press down.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees for electric oven or 350 degrees for gas.

title: cheese sausage biscuits
directions: Crumble sausage, mix in other ingredients until all blended. Form into balls place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown at 425°.
Makes 24 to 30.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
If made while pasta is still warm, you will probably have to re-taste and add more mayonnaise when it cools.

title: graham cracker candy
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and Pet milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium-high heat and boil for 7 or 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add graham cracker crumbs and pecans; stir until stiff. Spoon onto wax paper.
Let cool and store in airtight container.

title: golden nugget meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and mix well. Shape around cheese cube to make 16 meatballs.
Dredge in flour. Brown in bacon drippings over medium heat in a large skillet.
Pour off drippings.
Drain well. Pour tomato sauce over meatballs in skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Remove cover and simmer 5 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except 1 cup of nuts.
Roll in nuts.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In saucepan, bring to boil oleo, cocoa and water.
Add to flour and sugar mixture.
Beat and add eggs, buttermilk, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in 11 1/2 x 16-inch pan.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Clean and dice carrots.
Add butter, brown sugar and orange juice.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes until carrots are tender.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oleo on high speed until light and fluffy. Mix flour and vanilla on lower speed.
Pour on a sheet pan.
Drop desired fruit filling on dough and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix well.
Put in four 1-pound coffee cans that have been greased and dusted with flour.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Take out of cans and put on cookie rack to cool.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until clear.

Add the raw potatoes and chicken bouillon cube. Cover with water (just to top of potatoes). Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes start to fall apart and liquid begins to thicken (stir occasionally to keep from scorching). Mash with potato masher to consistency desired. For smoother soup, put in blender or use electric mixer.
On low heat, add the milk and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
This is good to sprinkle crumbled bacon or cheese on top.
Soup thickens when cold; you may add a little more milk to reheat.

title: zucchini rice casserole
directions: Note:
Be sure to measure dry rice out to equal two cups and then cook.

title: lemon angel food dessert
directions: Combine juice, sugar and milk.
Fold into whipped cream.
Add pineapple.
Break cake into bite-size pieces.
Put 1/2 cake in 9 x 13-inch pan and spoon over 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: peach layered cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place peaches and juice in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top (do not mix).
Sprinkle nut meats on top of cake mix.
Place chunks of cold oleo on top of nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Place buckwheat flour and white flour into a bowl.
Add enough warm water to make a thin batter.
Let sour.
Add soda, baking powder, salt and 1 teaspoon sugar to each cup of batter.
Fry pancakes until brown.
Add more flour and water to batter for later use.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Melt butter; add garlic, parsley, paprika, cayenne and wine and mix.
Place shrimp in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread butter mixture over and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until crumbs are brown.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Add beaten egg, shortening, orange juice and hot water.
Combine only until blended.
Fold in nuts, cranberries and orange rind.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in greased loaf pan.
When cool, store in refrigerator.

title: gone all afternoon stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Fold Cool Whip.
Spread in cooked pie shell.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spread coconut and nuts in pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mix over coconut and nuts in pan.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and sugar with mixer.
Pour this mixture on top of cake batter.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix margarine and stuffing mix.
Line a buttered baking dish with 1/2 stuffing mix. Layer chicken.
Add celery soup (diluted with 1/2 water) and layer again.
Add chicken soup (diluted with 1/2 water) and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cool whip dessert
directions: Take the margarine and melt in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Add pecans and flour; mix together and press into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Put cream cheese in small bowl.
Beat at low speed until slightly softened.
Add milk slowly and beat until blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and very thick. Spoon into crust.
Top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: fruit cake cobbler
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream the shortening.
Add sugar gradually; cream until light and fluffy.
Add part of the honey. Add flour mixture alternately, mixing well after each addition. Pour into greased pan or baking dish.
Place fruit or berries on top of batter.
Sprinkle with remaining honey and 1/4 cup sugar; dot with butter.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: remarkable fudge
directions: Butter sides of heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Combine milk and sugar.
Cook to soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove. Add chocolate pieces, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Whip bananas until light.
Cream butter and sugar and add eggs.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to butter and eggs.
Combine this mixture with the finely chopped pecans, then add crushed bananas.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield:
1 loaf.

title: cheddar artichoke puffs
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Cut pastry into 2 inch squares.
Top each square with 1 tablespoon mixture.
Top mixture with another pastry square.
Crimp edges with a fork to seal. Place on a well greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes. Serve with fancy toothpicks.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in blackberries and raisins which have been floured with part of the 3 cups of flour. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it leaves the pan.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and flavoring.
Add oats by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Sprinkle in bottom of a deep baking dish.
Pour sauce over and spread.
Spread half of cheese on top of sauce.
Layer pepperoni, ham, onion and bell pepper.
Top with remaining cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones.
In large pan, cook oleo, onions, celery and bell pepper until vegetables are limp.
Add soups and Velveeta cheese.
Add chicken, water chestnuts and cooked spaghetti or serve the spaghetti separately.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat and stir in next 4 ingredients.
Combine cracker crumbs and parsley flakes. Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain oysters, reserving 1/3 cup liquid. Sprinkle 1/2 cup cracker crumbs in bottom of lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish; layer half of oysters and half of remaining cracker crumb mixture.
Drizzle with half of the butter mixture.
Repeat layers.
Combine eggs, half and half and reserved oyster liquid.
Mix well.
Pour over oyster layers.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: key west conch chowder
directions: Mince or grind conch.
In olive oil saute onion, garlic and green pepper until soft but not browned.
Add bay leaves, tomato sauce and ground conch.
Cook about 30 minutes.
Add water and remaining seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Cook about one hour or until conch is tender and beginning to thicken. Add potatoes; cook 10 minutes or until tender.
For additional thickening, mash some of the potatoes against side of saucepan. Adjust seasonings to taste.
Add Tabasco.
Yield:
8 cups or 4 to 6 servings.

title: amaretto chocolate pie
directions: Prepare topping mix according to package instructions.
Add milk, pudding mix and Amaretto.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Pour mixture into 9-inch baked pie shell. Top with whipped topping and chocolate bits.
Chill at least four hours.

title: surprise lasagna
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish three times: spaghetti sauce, ground beef, cooked noodles to cover dish, grated Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and cottage cheese-yogurt mixture.
Cover tightly with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.
May be refrigerated overnight or frozen before baking.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Sift all ingredients together; stir thoroughly.
Store in closed container.
Mix 1/2 cup mixture to 1/2 cup boiling water or to taste.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and flour, beating well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until sufficiently browned.

title: chutney cheese ball
directions: Mix the Bleu cheese, cream cheese and chutney; form into a ball.
Roll the cheese ball in the chopped almonds.
Chill.
Serve with crackers (may be frozen).
Serves 7.

title: 8 minute cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; add in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Blend well; spoon in crust. Chill until set, about 4 hours.
Place strawberries on top.

title: a.1.  flavor meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients.
Pat into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat together and put in freezer.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with Bisquick mix. Dip coated chops into Italian dressing. Then coat with bread crumbs. Heat oil in a 12-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Cook pork about 5 minutes or until golden brown. Reduce heat to low. Carefully turn chops.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in potatoes, sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and 3 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in rest of flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and cover tightly.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours but no longer than 5 days.
Punch dough down.
Form into rolls and let rise. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add ingredients in order as listed. Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning, reserving 1 tablespoon.
In small bowl mix dressing, sugar, reserved taco mix and hot sauce.
In salad bowl put lettuce, tomatoes, onion and kidney beans.
Pour dressing over salad mixture.
Just before serving, toss in chips.

title: coconut cake(4 day cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Ice first layer; sprinkle coconut over icing. Ice second layer and sprinkle
coconut. Ice top and sides and sprinkle coconut. Wrap cake good with Glad Wrap and refrigerate for 4 days.

title: slow cooker cider
directions: Make a spice bag by placing cinnamon sticks, whole cloves and allspice in a double thickness of cheesecloth.
Bring up the corners of the cloth and tie it with a string to form a bag. Place the apple juice and brown sugar in a slow cooker and stir until the sugar dissolves.
Add the spice bag.
Cook on low setting for 2 to 5 hours.
Remove the spice bag before serving. Yield: 2 quarts.

title: holiday bread
directions: Cream together the Crisco and brown sugar.
Beat in the eggs and bananas.
Add plain flour, soda and baking powder.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips, dates and cherries.
Pour into two 7 3/4 x 3 1/4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Wrap and let set overnight before slicing.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and raisins.
Mix onion, bacon, sunflower seeds and broccoli.
Toss the 2 mixtures together; store in refrigerator.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Be sure apples are thinly diced or shredded.
Mix apples and raisins; add sugar.
Mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each.
Add oil, nuts and coconut.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture into batter.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: beef tips
directions: Bake all in casserole dish for 3 hours at 325°.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse.
Mix salad dressing with Salad Supreme.
Add veggies and toss together.
Refrigerate.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Make lemonade and drink mix according to package directions. Mix together and add thawed strawberries.
Add red food coloring for more color if desired.
Makes 24 servings at 1/2 cup each. This is easy but very good.

title: chess cake
directions: Cream together and pour over top.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 20.

title: creamy corn spoon bread
directions: Mix corn, margarine, sour cream, eggs and corn meal.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 1 hour.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the top.

title: buttermilk pies
directions: Combine sugar and flour; mix well.
Add beaten eggs, margarine and buttermilk; stir well to combine.
Add extracts.
Divide mixture between the pie shells, evenly.
Place in preheated 400° oven.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 45 minutes.
Top will brown and puff up but will settle down as it cools.
Tastes like an old fashioned egg custard.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3 1/2-quart saucepan and bring to boil on low.
Stir in peanut butter.
Take off heat.
Add cornflakes and stir until all are coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: jello pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter and add 2 tablespoons sugar and pretzels.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1/2 cup sugar; spread on top of baked pretzels.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water; add strawberries and mix well.
Refrigerate.
When it starts to set, pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: hamburger salami
directions: Mix well; put into covered bowl and let stand in fridge for 24 hours.
Make into logs usually five; wrap in foil so it's water tight.
Put into large pan; cover with cold water.
Bring to a boil and boil hard for 1 hour.
Cover with heavy plate when boiling.

title: apricot baked ham
directions: Score the surface of the ham with shallow diamond shaped cuts. Insert cloves in cuts.
Combine preserves and mustard; spread over ham.
Pat brown sugar over apricot mixture and place ham on a rack in a roasting pan.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 20 minutes per pound or until ham is heated through and thermometer reads 140 degrees.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar & brown sugar. Blend egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla. Stir in flour and oats. Spread in 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes. Sprinkle with chocolate chips. Let stand for 5 minutes to melt.
Then combine sifted powdered sugar, peanut butter and evaporated milk.	Mix well. Spread chocolate evenly after chips have melted.
Drizzle with peanut butter mixture.
Makes 24 bars.

title: holiday peppermint candy
directions: Beat cream cheese, margarine and syrup together; blend well. Add peppermint flavoring and 4 cups powdered sugar.
Mix well. Divide into thirds; knead few drops food coloring into each 1/3 (2); leave 1/3 white.

title: yum yum potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together (potatoes still frozen).
Pat into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until heated through.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball. Refrigerate.
Makes a pretty cheese ball for Christmas.

title: catskinner cake
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, 2 cups sugar, coconut, 3/4 cup buttermilk, oil, eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour batter in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese grits
directions: Pour grits into boiling water.
Add grated onion and salt. Cook 2 to 5 minutes as directed on grits box.
Add oleo, Cheez Whiz and Cheddar; season to taste with garlic powder and cayenne pepper.
When mixture has cooled slightly, add 2 eggs, beaten. Can be served as is, or baked in oven until bubbly.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper in hot fat until onion is golden.
Add soy sauce and tomato soup.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over noodles and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
More noodles can be added to stretch casserole.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Melt jelly and chili sauce together over low heat.
Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients and form meatballs.
Cook over medium heat until done.
Mix with jelly mixture and toss until covered. Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and milk. Add flour, drained corn, butter and seasonings. Cook at 400° for 45 minutes in covered casserole dish.

title: barry tea
directions: Put tea in boiling water.
Let set until clear.
Pour into half gallon pitcher.
Add sugar and dissolve.
Add cold water until the pitcher is 3/4 full, then add pineapple juice, grape juice and fresh lemon.
Serve with ice or hot.

title: cherry cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar; cut in margarine until like fine crumbs.
Add nuts and coconut.
Mix well; set aside 1/2 cup. Press remaining crumbs in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: kringles
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup butter and sour cream in bowl; mix well. Chill for 2 hours to overnight.
Divide dough into 4 portions. Roll each portion into 1/4-inch rectangles on floured surface. Spread rectangles with 1/2 cup butter.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and pecans.
Roll as for jelly roll, sealing ends and side.
Freeze for several hours.
Place frozen rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip for crackers
directions: Heat tomato soup.
Soften gelatin in cold water; add to soup. Mix in cream cheese until dissolved.
Cool in refrigerator, then fold in celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Fold in shrimp.
Chill. Serve with fancy crackers.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Let water, sugar, raisins and soda boil for 5 minutes; cool. Add shortening.
Let this mixture be completely cool and add flour, cinnamon, cloves, allspice, baking powder, pecans and gumdrops. Place in tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake 2 1/2 hours in 300° oven.
Store while hot in box.
Cover as soon as possible.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at
a time and beat. Add flour slowly. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Use 13 x 9 pan or bake in 3 (8-inch) layers. Grease and flour pans.

title: dried cranberry mazurkas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first 4 ingredients into a saucepan. Bring to a simmer. Cook over medium heat about 13 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and mixture is thick.
Spoon into blender or food processor and process until smooth; set aside.

title: easy baked rice
directions: Mix everything in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Cut 3/4 stick butter over the top.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Stir and bake 15 minutes longer or until water is absorbed.

title: onion salad dressing
directions: Blend the ingredients real good.
Add 2 cups oil; blend slowly.
Keep in refrigerator.
Good on most anything.

title: beef and eggplant casserole
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Add onion and pepper; cook about 2 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomato sauce, salt, oregano, basil and pepper.
Stir well to blend.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes. Place eggplant in buttered 13 3/4 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour meat mixture over eggplant.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Arrange cheese slices on meat.
Continue to bake 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: tropical soup
directions: Combine soup, milk and lime juice in a saucepan.
Blend thoroughly.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Chill for at least 6 hours.
Before serving, blend in banana and grapes. Garnish with lime rind and nutmeg.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomatoes, macaroni, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Brown chicken; drain off fat.
Season with salt and pepper. Add onion to skillet; blend in paprika.
Stir in wine, bouillon and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving platter; keep warm. Combine sour cream and flour; stir into liquid in skillet.
Heat, stirring until thick.
Serve with chicken over noodles.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts.
Blend until crumbly.
Set aside 2 cups.
Press remaining mixture into a 13 x 9-inch rectangular pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Beat together granulated sugar and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread over previously baked crust. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Continue baking for 25 minutes. Cool and cut.

title: aunt peggy's irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, sift dry ingredients.
Add raisins.
Mix egg, buttermilk and margarine together.
Combine with flour mixture. Knead lightly on a floured board.
Shape into a ball.
Place on a cookie sheet; flatten into a 7-inch circle.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until top is golden and loaf sounds hollow.
Brush top with melted margarine.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix together.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Top each serving with sour cream, shredded Cheddar cheese and crushed taco chips.

title: seven-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add 2 cups 7-Up. Add pineapple.
Let set.
Cook dressing of eggs, sugar, cornstarch and pineapple juice until it bubbles and thickens.
Cool.
Add 1/2 small Cool Whip (or 10 ounces) to cooled mixture.
Cover top of set jello mixture.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put all
ingredients
in
mixing
bowl; beat well; pour into a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pinto beans
directions: Wash beans. Cover with water and add seasonings. Let boil until beans are done. Just before serving, put 4 or 5 cut up Mexican hot links into the beans. Let boil for 5 or 10 minutes longer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salted boiling water; drain well. Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion and cheese.
Add drained broccoli; mix well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: escort chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted butter with crushed crackers.
Sprinkle 3/4 of cracker mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cut up chicken breasts over cracker mixture.
Layer water chestnuts.
Mix soups and sour cream.
If the mixture is too thick, add milk to thin. Pour mixture over the chicken and chestnuts.
Top with remaining crackers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in Tupperware holder or canister.
Use 2 teaspoons for each cup of water.
Add ice to glass and enjoy ice tea.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Break apart mei fun (rice noodles) and deep fry in hot oil, above 350°.
Noodles will fry within seconds and will be white and crisp when done.
Drain and set aside.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, mix sugar and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and chocolate chips. Stir.
(I use electric mixer.)
Just when you think you've stirred enough, you haven't so keep stirring until all the butter gets blended in and loses its gloss.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Store in refrigerator until firm.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Blend poppy seed and buttermilk; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next morning beat egg yolks, sugar and margarine together until fluffy.
Add poppy seed and buttermilk alternately with flour and baking soda, mixing well.
Add butter flavoring and almond extract; blend.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
